name: Protea Hotel Gaborone Masa Square
description:
My stay at Protea Hotel at Masa Square was actually really great . The room was spotless and well-prepared, with all the essentials thoughtfully provided. I especially appreciated the in-room fridge, which made it easy to store our own chilled drinks  a convenient touch.

The bathroom had consistent hot water, just as one would expect from a hotel of this standard. Breakfast each morning was excellent there was a wide variety of options, and everything was fresh, well-presented, and delicious.

The rooftop pool and outdoor bar added a unique and vibrant city experience that‚Äôs hard to find elsewhere in Gaborone. It‚Äôs the perfect place to unwind while enjoying beautiful views. The indoor gym was another plus ,fully equipped, clean, and clearly maintained with care.

Overall, the hotel met my expectations. I would gladly return and highly recommend it to anyone visiting the city.

name: Agua hotels Sal Vila Verde
description:
If we were to pay, say ¬£500 less, and they called it a 3-Star Hotel it would have met my partner's and my expectations. It is definitely not a 4-Star, and it is overpriced:

Customer Service - best we had was a pleasant welcome and helpful lady on reception. The staff around the pool bar, breakfast/dinner areas do not seem bothered at all with being there or creating positive guest experience. We had better customer service across different bars, restaurants and locations on our trip, so we don't believe it was a cultural difference, just poor customer service.

Food - If you're happy with "school dinner" quality and a lack of choice, you'll be ok. We're glad we weren't all-inclusive. Eating out was definitely the right choice here.

Hotel / Room - incredibly basic. Uncomfortable beds, door handles missing, sink plug not connected and getting stuck. Feels like a poor construction job. Oh and we were lucky enough to have a chronic smoker next door stinking out the whole floor. üôÑ

We had a fantastic time in Cape Verde, unfortunately this hotel did not add to the experience at all. An honest review we hope gets listened too and to advise others.

name: Luano International Airport
description:
Unfortunately, one of the most challenging airport experiences I've encountered. The terminal facilities are in very poor condition. Upon arrival, baggage collection is chaotic, with luggage unceremoniously dropped by a tractor and no staff guiding passengers. Be wary of individuals offering unsolicited "help" with bags; they will  demand payment. Crucially, do NOT give anyone your baggage claim ticket.

Departures are equally disorganized. There's no clear separation between local and international passengers, leading to crowded and confusing areas with minimal signage or direction. Again, expect staff to approach offering 'assistance' and then aggressively demand payment (expect $10+). Check-in and security procedures are highly inefficient; all luggage is manually inspected as there are no scanners, so keep a close eye on your bags to prevent loss. Be prepared for a mandatory and enforced $55 airport tax, and health officials may demand payment for alleged typhoid and cholera vaccinations ($10). There's one duty-free shops which is mostly closed and a very tiny restaurant. The waiting lounge is in disrepair. Come prepared for significant challenges.

name: Nigeria Embassy in C√¥te d'Ivoire
description:
The Nigerian Embassy in Abidjan, Cote d'Ivoire, serves as the official diplomatic representation of Nigeria in the country. It is a crucial hub for fostering diplomatic relations, providing consular services, and facilitating interactions between Nigeria and Cote d'Ivoire.

The embassy is likely to be equipped with various departments, including consular, political, and administrative sections, each dedicated to specific functions. Visitors to the embassy can expect to find a range of services such as visa processing, passport issuance, and assistance with legal and administrative matters related to Nigerian citizens in Cote d'Ivoire.

The embassy is located in Plateau. Contact information, and operational hours can be obtained from official sources or through the Nigerian government's official channels.

The Indian restaurant is not bad. Halal food. Decent service and big portions. I ended up having to do take away to share ‚Ä¶ they have no sense of dinner background music. name: Omali S√£o Tom√©
description:
After two weeks of traveling on Pr√≠ncipe and S√£o Tom√©, we ended our trip at Omali as we really craved some relaxation and comfort. We were not disappointed. Since we traveled with our son, we were assigned the (pretty expensive) family suite, which is huge and beautiful, with truly amazingly comfortable beds. Five stars for the hotel - but the self-proclaimed enclosed ‚Äúbest restaurant on S√£o Tom√©‚Äù was somewhat disappointing.

I‚Äôm not usually one to complain on destinations such as STP, but with prices like Omali‚Äôs and the pretentious image they aim to project, I would expect top quality all around. Here‚Äôs what happened: from the menu I ordered ‚Äúpan-fried steak with Omali mustard sauce.‚Äù The waiter asked me if I wanted it rare, medium, or well done. I chose medium-rare, but the steak I was served was thoroughly cooked. When I pointed this out, the waiter looked confused, took the steak away, and came back with an even more cooked one. At that point, I gave up, as he clearly did not understand (we don‚Äôt speak Portuguese).

I did, however, ask about the missing ‚Äúmustard sauce.‚Äù Again I got a confused look, and was asked to show what I meant on the menu. I pointed out the Portuguese description, and the waiter eventually returned‚Ä¶ with a bowl of the same gravy the steak had been cooked in.

name: Bakaara Market
description:
Bakaara Market, located in Mogadishu, Somalia, is a bustling and historically significant open-air market. It is the largest market in the country and a central hub for trade and commerce.
Here's a review of what you can expect, based on available information:
Overview of the Market
* Size and Scope: Bakaara is a massive market, often described as a city within a city. It's the economic heart of Mogadishu, selling everything from daily essentials like maize, sorghum, beans, and other food items to clothing, household goods, and even building materials and gold.
* Historical Significance: The market was established in the early 1970s. It has a complex history, having been a center of conflict and a stronghold for various militias and extremist groups in the past. However, in recent years, with the withdrawal of Al-Shabaab from the capital, it has been revitalized and is now a symbol of Mogadishu's economic recovery.
* Goods and Products: You can find a wide variety of goods here. While it's known for daily necessities, it has also historically been associated with illicit activities, such as the sale of counterfeit documents and weapons. Today, the focus is more on legitimate trade, including a large and vibrant livestock market.
Customer Experience
* Atmosphere: The market is described as incredibly lively, crowded, and loud. It's a sensory experience, with a constant buzz of activity, from vendors calling out to customers to the general hustle and bustle of a major commercial center.
* Safety and Security: The market's reputation for safety has been a major concern in the past due to sporadic violence and conflict. However, reports suggest that with increased security measures and the stabilization of Mogadishu, it is generally considered safer than it once was. Nonetheless, it's still a place that requires a high degree of caution, especially for foreign visitors. It is highly recommended to have a knowledgeable local guide.
* Cleanliness and Organization: Some recent accounts mention that the market is "surprisingly somewhat too clean," with organized stores and bright lights. This suggests that there have been significant improvements in the market's infrastructure and management. However, it's still a busy, open-air market, so you can expect a degree of dirt and mud, particularly at entrances.
* Food: The market is a great place to find local food. Some visitors have mentioned "shack-like 'restaurants'" with delicious food and generous portions.
* Interaction with Locals: Visitors can expect to be called out by vendors, often respectfully, encouraging them to visit their stores. People are generally described as friendly and welcoming, but it's an environment where you'll get a lot of attention.
In summary, Bakaara Market is a fascinating and essential part of Mogadishu. It represents both the challenges and the resilience of the city. While it has a troubled past, it is now a thriving economic hub that offers a unique and authentic glimpse into daily life in Somalia. Visiting requires awareness and a cautious approach, but it can be a rewarding experience.

name: Vijana Mall
description:
Last weekend, I decided to explore Vijana Mall, a relatively new and rising commercial center that I had heard quite a bit about. The mall is located in a strategic area that‚Äôs easily accessible by both private and public transport, which made getting there simple and convenient.

First Impressions:
As I arrived, the first thing that caught my eye was the modern architecture of the building. The design is sleek, with clean glass panels and bold signage. The entrance was wide and welcoming, with security personnel politely guiding visitors in. There was a clear sense of order and safety, which gave me a good first impression.

Interior and Layout:
Inside, the mall is well-organized, with wide corridors, bright lighting, and clear signboards that make navigation very easy. It has three floors, each offering a mix of retail, service, and leisure spaces. The ground floor is mostly taken up by local fashion boutiques, electronics shops, and a few well-known fast-food outlets.

Shops and Services:
One thing I appreciated was the variety of businesses housed in the mall. I came across youth-owned shops selling creative streetwear, handmade crafts, and even custom phone accessories. There‚Äôs a mobile repair hub that was quite busy, and several salons and barber shops offering affordable grooming services.

On the second floor, there were more service-oriented businesses like travel agencies, microfinance offices, and a cyber caf√©. The top floor is partly dedicated to a co-working space and a small event hall that‚Äôs often rented for business expos or youth trainings.

Food Court and Social Vibe:
The food court is one of the highlights. It offers both local Tanzanian dishes and international options like pizza, shawarma, and smoothies. The prices were fair, and the service was quick. I sat at a corner table overlooking the street and enjoyed a fresh plate of chips mayai with a cold soda.

What really stood out to me was the vibrant energy of the mall. It was filled with young entrepreneurs, creatives, and students‚Äîsome were networking, some shopping, others just hanging out. There was even a small pop-up stand for a youth-run business selling natural skincare products.

Final Thoughts:
Vijana Mall isn‚Äôt just a place to shop‚Äîit‚Äôs a hub of youth innovation and enterprise. It promotes local talent and creates opportunities for young people to showcase their skills and build their brands. I left feeling inspired by the energy and creativity in that space.

Whether you‚Äôre looking to shop, eat, connect, or even start a business, Vijana Mall is definitely worth a visit.

name: Tamuka Travel
description:
I was so excited about that activity and it didn‚Äôt disappoint! My driver, Brighton, was there perfectly on time, and really helpful and friendly. We got there really easily in a comfy vehicle. The activity itself was WAW! Through the photos it seems chill and everything but it‚Äôs actually a real adventure making it even more rewarding. After it you‚Äôll think to yourself ‚Äúwow, did I really do that?!‚Äù. The staff was really helpful and is feel safe at any time! I went for breakfast and the food was good with water available to refill your bottle if needed.

Tips :
- you need to be able to swim as you‚Äôve to swim across some path with a bit of current (not too much tho) but it‚Äôs perfectly safe as there are ropes and really amazing staff to help you.
- bring your own waterproof shoes with grip or rent some for 2$ at the departure. You will need it! No flipflops (you gonna loose them in the falls anyway except if you‚Äôve a good toe-grip haha)!
- a clean towel is included after the swim so no need to bring yours, carrying a huge backpack and looking like a teenage mutant ninja turtle
- try the loo-with-view on the island itself. Not everyday you got to go to toilets with view on the Victoria falls

name: Wild Horizons
description: The sunset cruise on the Zambezi river was a magical experience‚Äîrelaxing, scenic, and well organized. We saw hippos while enjoying unlimited drinks and delicious snacks. name: The Lookout Cafe - Wild Horizons
description: What a fun experience! Absolutely loved my sirloin steak, cooked to perfection. Our waiter was energetic and very efficient. The only thing I didn‚Äôt quite enjoy was our seating spot, would have much rather preferred a better view of the gorge. I suggest booking way in advance if you want to enjoy the full experience. I also recommend the crocodile kebab, so tender and flavorful. The French fries were so good, a unique crunchiness and flavor to them. Definitely a must-visit if you‚Äôre in Vic Falls

name: Victoria Falls Safari Club
description:
Truly incredible stay here! It was so luxurious and clean, and our room had a gorgeous view. The Lodge is in front of a watering hole which we could see from our room and the dining area. We saw so many elephants and zebras, it was incredible to see them during dinner each night.

The staff were exceptional, always attentive and friendly. There were multiple staff who stood out including Dennis who took care of us the whole time. The hotel also had a regular bus service into town which we took to Victoria Falls and to take out cash.

We also did a day trip safari to Botswana through the hotel which was just unforgettable. The hotel arranged us being driven to Botswana and back, as well as the safari itself. Would recommend getting the double Zimbabwe Visa on arrival if you want to do that.

We spent our last day at the hotel pool with drinks and sun, and saw the vulture feeding they do.

Can‚Äôt recommend this place enough!

name: THE PEMA BY REALM
description:
Whether you're on holiday or travelling for business, The Pema is an impeccable choice in terms of service, comfort, and privacy. From the warm and affable greeting on arrival, to the thoughtful gifts and choice of toiletries in the room (from meaningful and sustainable small businesses in Bhutan and Thailand), I felt they paid good attention to detail at this establishment. All the staff were helpful, well trained, and friendly.

The room was well-sized, with a very comfortable bed and luxurious bathroom fittings. I was jetlagged from a prior work trip and managed to get a proper rest during my two nights here. Some commenters said the street dogs bark through the night, but this was not a problem for me (really not that much barking, and it sounded far off).

I highly recommend the massage with the singing bowls! It was top notch-- unique, utterly relaxing, and the masseuse was very kind and skillful.

Dinner and breakfast in the ground floor bistro is ala carte, with both local and international choices that were always generously portioned. I would gladly stay here again if I need to be in Thimphu!

name: Global Reach Education Consultancy in Bhutan
description:
My experience with Global Reach Bhutan has been incredibly positive, especial thanks to my counsellor, Mam KC. She supported me through every step of the journey‚Äînot just during office hours, but even late at night. I‚Äôm truly grateful to her and the entire consultancy team for providing clear, detailed guidance on what needed to be done, how to go about it, and when, which made the whole process much easier to manage.

Even though I had previously faced a visa refusal and other consultancies declined to take on my case, Global Reach stood by me and delivered exceptional service. Their strong ties and professional relationships with universities helped ease the process and made the path to qualification feel far less intimidating.

After several months of preparing documents and following the necessary procedures, I‚Äôm excited to share that I‚Äôve been granted a student visa to study at the University of Adelaide. I wholeheartedly recommend Global Reach Education Consultancy to any student or couple planning to pursue their studies abroad.

name: Paro Taktsang
description:
The Tigers Nest Monastery (Paro Taktsang) trek in Bhutan is a breathtaking experience!

Trek Highlights

1. Scenic views‚Äî‚ÄîStunning Himalayan landscapes and valleys.

2. Cultural significance‚Äî‚ÄîVisit the iconic monastery, a sacred site for Bhutanese Buddhists.

3. Challenging yet rewarding‚Äî‚ÄîThe trek is moderately difficult, but the scenery and sense of accomplishment make it worthwhile.

Trek Details

1. Duration‚Äî‚ÄîApproximately 4-6 hours round trip.
2. Distance‚Äî‚ÄîAround 10 km round trip.
3. Altitude‚Äî‚ÄîStarts at 2,800 meters and reaches 3,120 meters at the monastery.
4. Respect local customs‚Äî‚ÄîDress modestly and follow monastery rules.

The trek offers:

1. Serenity‚Äî‚ÄîPeaceful surroundings and spiritual ambiance.
2. inspiring views‚Äî‚Äî‚ÄîPanoramic vistas of the Himalayas.
3. Cultural immersion‚Äî‚Äî‚ÄîInsights into Bhutanese Buddhism and traditions.

description:
We recently stayed 3 nights in this hotel (March 2025) We were very lucky in our room allocation as it had a veranda which overlooked the pool. The room was massive with 2 double beds and a lovely bathroom. Even though the room was directly above the reception it was very quiet. The bed was comfortable and all toiletries were provided free of charge. The room was very clean and the house staff did an excellent job of keeping it so. I was unwell for 24 hours and I must say the staff went out of their way to do all they could to help. They provided free tea and toast, delivering it to the room. I cannot praise the staff enough. name: Veralofts | Aura
description:
It is very unfortunate, however I have to leave a negative review for this location of Vera Lofts. There are several reasons why I won‚Äôt be recommending Vera Lofts to anyone:

-I didn‚Äôt gain entry of the space until close to 45 minutes after my rental time had started. My timeslot was from 10-12, I didn‚Äôt get access to the space until 10:42, my first photoshoot was at 10:45. So you‚Äôre paying $200 to rent a space that you may or may not gain access to- depending on if the owner of the space hears his phone.
Speaking of which:

- For a company with very specific instructions to call the owner of the space for permission to access the space, they were very lackadaisical about answering their phone- which is a google number, the only phone number provided for the business. I called them no less than 10 times, before contacting their instagram page, and calling 2 more times before someone finally picked up. At that point, my clients were already there, and I had less than 5 minutes before their shoot time was supposed to start. After a brief exchange where the owner tried to blame-shift (he didn‚Äôt ‚Äòsee that I had called that many times‚Äô) I learned that the entry code they give in the email was all I needed, and that I didn‚Äôt need to call in order to access, it was just a courtesy to call- their instructions didn‚Äôt give that impression, at all.

- my message to the owner of Vera Lofts on instagram in general simply was read, there was no apology, there is no acknowledgment of my message, no response whatsoever. The whole exchange was very piss poor. I did make a request for a refund- perhaps that prompted the lack of response.
- In order to accommodate for my time loss, they saw it fit to give me the time I lost  in the following timeslot. However, that was not a proper solution. my photo shoots were planned for the timeslot that I paid for, so I would literally just be sitting in the space with no reason to use said space.
- And to top it all off, the space was much, MUCH dimmer than advertised, it is extremely dark in the indoor portion of the space, and there are boxes/containers visible in some aspects of the space.
So overall, it was a negative experience. It seems they are fine tailored to take your money, but are definitely lacking in customer care and coming up with proper solutions to accommodate mistakes made on their part- that‚Äôs too much of an investment made on the client‚Äôs part for them not to be performing in excellence. I‚Äôll definitely be warning as many photographers that I can about them.

description:
Hotel Chakra in Saki Naka is a great spot if you're looking for quality food and a comfortable atmosphere just 5 minutes‚Äô walk from the Saki Naka metro station. The ambience is warm, clean, and inviting‚Äîideal for both casual outings and small gatherings.

The service here stands out. Staff are polite, attentive, and quick without being overbearing. Even when the place gets a bit busy, they handle things smoothly, which adds to the overall experience.

The food is the real highlight. Must-try dishes include their crispy **masala papad** to start, followed by the delicious **paneer chilly** and **chana koliwada with garlic**‚Äîboth bursting with flavor. For mains, the **mushroom cheese stuffed dish**, **chicken masala**, and **chicken tikka masala** are excellent choices, especially when paired with their **butter naan** and **kulcha**. Everything is well-prepared, and the spice levels are just right.

Portion sizes are generous, and the quality matches the price. For a group of 4‚Äì5 people (2 veg, 3 non-veg), expect to spend around ‚Çπ4500, which is quite reasonable for the variety and quantity offered.

Overall, Hotel Chakra offers great food, good service, and a pleasant atmosphere‚Äîdefinitely worth visiting if you're in the Saki Naka area.

description:
I would like to share my review of Aurora Parlour located in Purbachal Haltu. Overall, my experience at Aurora Parlour was exceptional.

The ambiance of the parlour was delightful, creating a soothing and relaxing atmosphere. The decor was tastefully done, with attention to detail, creating a visually appealing space.

The staff members at Aurora Parlour were friendly, professional, and attentive. They greeted me warmly upon arrival and made me feel comfortable throughout my visit. Their knowledge and expertise in their respective services were evident, and they provided excellent recommendations based on my preferences.

The parlour offers a wide range of services, catering to various beauty and wellness needs. I availed myself of their hair styling and skincare services, and I was thoroughly impressed with the results. The stylists and aestheticians were skilled and attentive to my specific requirements, ensuring a satisfying experience.

Hygiene and cleanliness are given utmost importance at Aurora Parlour. I observed that strict protocols were followed, and all tools and equipment were sanitized before use. This aspect provided an additional sense of trust and comfort during my visit.

In terms of pricing, I found the services at Aurora Parlour to be reasonable and value for money. They offer competitive rates for the quality of services provided.

Overall, I highly recommend Aurora Parlour in Purbachal Haltu for anyone seeking professional beauty and wellness services. From the welcoming ambiance to the skilled staff members, my experience was nothing short of excellent. I look forward to visiting again in the future.

Note: This review reflects my personal experience and opinions at Aurora Parlour, Purbachal Haltu. Others may have different experiences and perspectives.

name: Aura By Area83 - Luxury weddings & Events Venue
description:
Aura just hosted our wedding on the 29th and 30th of April 2025, the place got recommended by a friend of my mother in law‚Äôs who had also hosted another event there before, they recommended this place because my wife and I wanted to have a water body present at the venue, but to our surprise the venue has a floating deck which is where our mantapa was setup for all the main ceremonies.

We started talking to the venue around 6 months before the event and started planning it, our points of contact Sunil L and Kenneth were an absolute delight to work with.

Sunil, their in house event manager, and also pretty much the venue manager at aura spent countless hours with us during decor planning, he patiently listened to everything we had to say about our vision for the event and recommended his own unique ideas that would work within our theme.

Sunil was available on call 24x7 during the event and the 3 days prior to our event, he made sure he did everything within his power to fulfil our last minute special requests, he even helped set one of our guests up in his office because they had to take a work call on the evening of 29th

It was surreal to have witnessed all the ideas we presented and Sunil also presented come to life on the day of the event, there was a welcome ceremony my side of the family had to do before we kicked things off on the 29th and walking through the stairway and seeing all the decor elements setup up so beautifully was a experience I get to cherish for the rest of my life.

Everything we were worried about or thought might stress us out on the day of was handled beautifully by Sunil and his team and they ensured everything flowed Seamlessly.
Highly recommending aura to peers and family in the future for their events

description:
A Magical Evening Thanks to Aura Events!

I recently had the pleasure of entrusting Aura Events, led by the dynamic duo Rose and Mathew, with the event management for my brother-in-law's wedding reception. I am beyond impressed with the exceptional service and magical touch they brought to the celebration.

From the initial planning stages to the execution of every detail, Rose and Mathew exhibited unmatched professionalism, creativity, and dedication. Their meticulous attention to detail ensured that every aspect of the event was flawlessly executed, leaving us to enjoy the festivities stress-free.

The decor was nothing short of spectacular ‚Äì a perfect blend of elegance and the couple's unique style. The ambiance they created was enchanting, setting the stage for a night to remember. The team's ability to transform our vision into reality truly exceeded our expectations.

What stood out most was the seamless coordination throughout the evening. Rose and Mathew were present at every moment, ensuring that the schedule flowed smoothly. Their team's efficiency and warmth were evident, making everyone feel comfortable and allowing us to fully immerse ourselves in the celebration.

I want to express my deepest gratitude to Aura Events for turning our dream reception into a reality. It was not just an event; it was a magical experience that will be etched in our memories forever. I wholeheartedly recommend Rose and Mathew to anyone seeking not just event management but a team that genuinely cares about making your special day extraordinary.

Thank you, Aura Events, for making my brother-in-law's wedding reception an absolute fairy tale!

name: The Cakra Hotel
description:
Really great place to stay and relax, has a ton of facilities like pools, 24hour gym and the food is also great. Stayed here while I was sick and it was a nice time to recover. Service is also excellent!

Would be back if I ever visit the area again.

EDIT: Had to come back to rewrite this review due to a recent incident.

While at the 4m deep pool, we were unfortunate to have encountered a young man who was alongside us who ended up drowning despite our best efforts to save him. In the process, we were trying to perform CPR and looking for an AED to revive him, however, none of the staff available at the time were trained. This meant that they were unable to assist us, and when the ambulance arrived, none were also confident enough to follow the poor man to the hospital. As a result, a couple of my friends (guests at the hotel) were the ones who had to help the man.

When asked about this, the hotel said the pool should be closed at 6pm. This incident happened around 7pm. So, where are  the safety precautions in place?

1. There is no lifeguard for a 4 metre deep pool.

2. There is no enforcement of the pool closure rules.

The hotel staff merely told us they thought it would be fine because we were in a big group.

Is this truly justified?

name: Aurora Place Bukit Jalil
description:
Got it! Here‚Äôs the updated Malaysian-style review with your input included:

‚∏ª

Aurora Place @ Bukit Jalil Review

Aurora Place is not really a shopping mall you walk around for fun, but if you happen to work or stay nearby, it‚Äôs actually quite convenient to drop by. Got makan places, cafes, some offices, clinics, and even a gym ‚Äì so everything also ada sikit-sikit.

Even though not much to explore like a full-blown mall, if you walk here from nearby condos or Pavilion Bukit Jalil, it‚Äôs still very accessible. There‚Äôs even a link bridge straight to Pavilion, so quite senang if you want to avoid the crowd and just chill somewhere quieter.

Food-wise, not bad ‚Äì got variety. From local stalls to Korean BBQ, Japanese restaurants, and a few nice coffee places to lepak or do laptop work. Weekend sometimes got pop-up stalls downstairs, so got a bit of life here and there.

Parking is usually okay, and not too expensive. Security and cleanliness also boleh tahan. Good place to settle errands or grab a quick bite without squeezing through a packed mall.

Overall, maybe not a place to purposely come jalan-jalan, but for nearby residents or office crowd ‚Äì memang convenient.

description:

The resort had an amazing selection of restaurants, and I was particularly fond of the Thai and Italian options. The food was delicious, and the service was top-notch.

I also loved the variety of water sports and activities available, which added an exciting element to my stay. But what really drew me to this resort was the tranquil atmosphere, perfect for chilling, healing, and indulging in some luxury. The Indian Ocean air seemed to melt all my worries away!

Overall, Centara Grand Island Resort & Spa Maldives exceeded my expectations in every way. If you're looking for a luxurious, relaxing getaway, this is the place to be!

The other restaurants also served exceptional plates with top-quality ingredients and presentation. The lagoon was stunning, perfect for snorkeling right off the beach. Our child loved the kids‚Äô club, which was thoughtfully run and full of engaging activities. All the staff were incredibly friendly, and our butler, Ahmed, provided professional and amazing service‚Äîarranging all our bookings and schedules with great care.

If there‚Äôs one thing to be desired, it would be the pricing of food and beverages, which felt quite high even for a luxury resort. That said, everything else was finely curated for both relaxation and adventure. Highly recommend!

name: Jumeirah Olhahali Island Maldives
description:
If you're dreaming of the ultimate luxury getaway, Jumeirah Olhahali Island in the Maldives is the perfect destination. From the moment I arrived, every aspect of this stunning property exceeded my expectations and made my stay unforgettable.
The food was absolutely phenomenal. Each meal was a masterpiece, showcasing incredible flavors and attention to detail. Whether it was freshly caught seafood or beautifully plated desserts, every bite was a treat to the senses. Dining here felt like a culinary adventure, and the variety of options ensured there was something appealing for every palate.
The butler service was impeccable. The staff went above and beyond to ensure my needs were met, always with a smile and a professional touch. They anticipated my requests before I even made them, making me feel truly cared for throughout my stay. It‚Äôs clear that guest satisfaction is their top priority.
My accommodation was a dream. The living conditions were luxurious, spacious, and thoughtfully designed, blending modern elegance with the natural beauty of the island. Waking up to breathtaking ocean views each day was something I‚Äôll never forget. The attention to detail in every corner of my villa made it feel like a piece of paradise.
The pools were another highlight. Whether it was the private pool in my villa or the main infinity pool overlooking the vast blue ocean, the experience was nothing short of extraordinary. Each swim was both refreshing and serene, with the gorgeous surroundings adding a special touch.
The amenities and overall experience were top-tier. From the water sports to the spa treatments, every aspect was curated to create memories I‚Äôll cherish forever. The island itself is beautifully maintained, and the seamless blend of natural beauty and luxurious comfort left me in awe.
Jumeirah Olhahali Island in the Maldives is the epitome of perfection. It‚Äôs more than just a resort; it‚Äôs an experience that stays with you. I can‚Äôt recommend it enough and am already counting down the days until I can return to this slice of paradise.

name: SM Seaside City Cebu
description:
SM Seaside Cebu is one of the largest malls in the Philippines, offering a vast and impressive shopping experience. With its modern architecture, high ceilings, and wide walkways, the mall is designed to give visitors a spacious and airy feel. Inside, you‚Äôll find a variety of stores, from luxury brands to more affordable local shops, as well as electronics, home goods, and beauty products. There‚Äôs something for every shopper, making it a perfect destination for anyone looking to indulge in a day of retail therapy.

The food scene at SM Seaside Cebu is another standout feature. The mall has an extensive range of dining options, from casual food courts with local and international fast food to upscale restaurants offering delicious meals with beautiful views of the city and ocean. We tried some restaurants during our visit, and although we didn‚Äôt make it to the bar, it was still a great experience. For those looking to relax and unwind, the Sky Park on the top floor is a peaceful outdoor space with benches, cafes, and a stunning view, making it an ideal spot for an afternoon break or evening stroll.

We also had a blast trying out the bowling and archery at the mall. Both activities were fun and added an extra layer of excitement to our visit. Whether you‚Äôre looking for something active or just want to enjoy some downtime, SM Seaside Cebu has a variety of options to keep you entertained. The mall is easy to access, with ample parking and a family-friendly atmosphere. Whether you're shopping, dining, or enjoying the many attractions, it‚Äôs a destination that truly has something for everyone.

While we were waiting, we explored the mall and checked out the different tenants. We found quite a variety of shops and restaurants. Their food hall is aesthetically pleasing, and we decided to have lunch at Zubuchon. The food was delicious!

After lunch, we indulged in some pampering. Jay got a foot spa, and I had my lashes done at Stylash. I loved it!

The mall‚Äôs building is a mix of old and new. Some parts are still the original SM, while others have undergone renovations.

Overall, it was a great experience. :)

name: Cebu Exchange Tower
description:
Subject: Concern on Waiting Area and Guard Conduct at Cebu Exchange Tower

I‚Äôm writing to raise a concern regarding an incident I experienced today at the Cebu Exchange Tower.

Earlier, I was waiting for my cousin at the open space across Union Bank, which seemed like a reasonable and safe waiting spot. After a short while, a guard approached me and told me that waiting there was not allowed and pointed me toward the entrance area instead ‚Äî a location where people are constantly walking by. I was confused because the area I was in appeared to be a proper space for waiting.

I understand that the guards are just doing their job and following protocol, and I respect that. However, the situation was confusing and a bit frustrating, as there were no signs indicating that waiting in that area was prohibited. It made me wonder ‚Äî what exactly is the purpose of that space? If it‚Äôs not meant for waiting, then perhaps the management can consider placing clear signage, or better yet, creating a designated waiting area.

I‚Äôve also noticed similar instances in the past where guards were somewhat abrupt when approaching riders. While I understand the need to keep the area organized, a little more courtesy and clarity would really help create a more welcoming environment.

I‚Äôm sharing this not to cause trouble, but in the hope that improvements can be made for the benefit of everyone visiting your building.

name: AMANOR Hotel Chiang Mai
description:
I can not say enough good things about this very Chic hotel to do it justice! The service was phenomenal! Especially considering I booked last minute. The front desk was amazing answering the questions I had and providing suggestions when needed. I also put in a request without filling out the proper form, and although I was on an excursion for the day. They filled my request and made it express as I was leaving the next day. The restaurant was great, as well as the rooftop bar.
I picked the area because of the ability to walk to cafes, boutiques, restaurants and nightlife. I often took a 15min Grab to Old Town for the Temples, Night market etc. this hotel was the perfect location for me with amazing service. I will be returning and will stay a lot longer in Chiang Mai as it became one of my fav places to visit in Thailand!

name: Aurora Club Cm
description:
Terrible Experience ‚Äì Felt Like a Total Rip-Off

Avoid Aurora Club CM at all costs. This place is nothing more than a money trap dressed up as a club. The attitude of the staff ‚Äî especially the girls ‚Äî was downright rude and dismissive. From the moment I walked in, it was clear they weren‚Äôt interested in offering any kind of good service ‚Äî just in how fast they could drain your wallet.

There was zero effort to make the experience enjoyable or even remotely welcoming. The girls were uninterested, cold, and clearly only pretending to engage to get tips or upsell overpriced services. I left feeling scammed ‚Äî like my money had been stolen in broad daylight.

No professionalism, no respect, no value for money ‚Äî just a hollow, uncomfortable experience. If you‚Äôre looking to relax, have fun, or even just be treated decently, this is NOT the place. Total waste of time and money. You've been warned.

name: Chakra
description:
It's a brand I like very much. It definitely has a line in terms of style. The products are expensive but seriously high quality. The window display is very successful, the decoration is wonderful, it is a simple store that does not tire people. The lighting is very successful, it is one of the rare brands/stores where you can walk around in peace and where the products are not stacked as if they are about to collapse. There is even harmony in the product colors. The only thing I would criticize about this place is this, that's why I took off one star. It's probably because it's told to employees, but this kind of approach is a thing of the past. You want to go in and walk around, but a staff member constantly walks 1 meter behind you, and when you take 2 steps, he moves too. What were you looking at? Brother, I didn't look at anything, I'm just wandering around, maybe something will catch my attention, it's a product that I haven't planned before, I won't shop on purpose, maybe I'll buy it when I see it. I'll like it at that moment, maybe I'll buy it when I don't even think about it. I entered it many times, I got the same treatment, believe me, I don't enter it anymore. It is a spotlessly clean store, the shelves are always neat, not messy, everything is placed in an orderly manner, they fix it immediately after distribution. It looks shiny.
Also, during this pandemic period, those who enter are not asked for their HES code and there is no temperature check. This place is located within Bilkent Center but on the ground floor. You can park your car in the Lower Car Park and enter the store directly without any questions. There is no control. When entering the Milkrnt Center shopping area, yes, there is a HES code inquiry and temperature measurement while passing through the door, but this area is outside that area. You can enter directly. I couldn't find it suitable for such a brand. I am currently sitting on the benches in the middle area and watching for 20 minutes. They do not control those who enter in any way, and this is a very important deficiency. Such brands need to pioneer some things and set an example.
07/04/2021

The interior design is equally stunning, with an elegant yet contemporary vibe that feels both luxurious and inviting. Every detail, from the lighting to the furniture, has been thoughtfully curated to enhance the overall experience.

The bar boasts an impressive selection of gin, with options ranging from classics to rare finds, and the cocktail menu is a creative masterpiece. Each drink is artfully crafted, balancing flavors in ways that delight even the most discerning palate.

What truly elevates this place, however, is the impeccable service. The staff is attentive, knowledgeable, and genuinely passionate about what they do, always ready to recommend the perfect cocktail or provide insights into the gins on offer.

Whether you‚Äôre celebrating a special occasion, entertaining clients, or simply indulging in a night out, the 50th floor bar at the Ritz-Carlton is an experience worth savoring. It‚Äôs not just a bar‚Äîit‚Äôs a destination.

name: Aurora Queen Resort
description:
Would 10 out of 10 recommend staying at AQR if you find yourself planning a trip Saariselka, Finland. We stayed for two nights in late March and had a wonderful experience.
Service
The owners and hosts are incredibly attentive and kind. From your initial greeting to send off Nina and Pasi make you feel like valued patrons of an exclusive experience. The staff is also kind and accommodating, with great recommendations and knowledge of the surrounding area. We also booked all excursions through the resort which made coordination very convenient. We enjoyed the aurora hunting and husky excursion, both were very enjoyable. The main dining had great breakfast included, limited lunch options, and delicious rotating dinner menu.
Location
Located only 35 minutes from Ivalo airport the resort was easy to get to and the resort also offers arranged transportation, for a reasonable fee.
Room
The rooms were great with great scenic views from the room. There is a dedicated small space for luggage and clothes to be hung along with a bathroom that‚Äôs small but luxurious. We enjoyed the room overall, however I‚Äôll note there is no way to block the morning sun and no full length mirror.

name: Aurora Village Oy
description:
This place is AMAZING! The staff is super friendly and accommodating, they kept lunch open late for us, and opened breakfast early for us, due to our booked activities overlapping dining times. From the very start the staff was just amazing.

They offer loads of fun activities that include all your winter gear you need. I recommend all the activities that are available, we loved every single thing we did.

The cabin itself is just stunning, we saw the Aurora lights every evening right from our bed. The property lights aren‚Äôt too bright, so it‚Äôs perfect to spot the lights from the property. The whole design and location of this place is just perfect. They offer free snow shoes/skis to go off and explore on your own, which I really recommend, because the property is so big and beautiful.

The restaurant was really yummy, we didn‚Äôt have one bad meal the whole time we were there. So sad to be leaving this beautiful place.

name: Aurora Service Tours
description:
Such a highlight of our trip to Finland! Tony runs a small but full-service Lapland tour in Utsjoksi, up in the north of the country, directly across the border from Norway.

The location at nearly 70 degree north latitude means you‚Äôre more likely to see the Aurora Borealis (though it ultimately comes down to a combination of the magnetosphere activity, weather and some luck).

The cabins were super cozy with washing machine, drying cabinet, dishwasher, fridge, showers, fireplace, and of course its own sauna. We stayed in their Asgaard B cottages which are their newest and come with the above amenities.

We chose a 4 night stay and saw the Aurora every night except for the last when we got a pretty big snowstorm. Some nights we viewed the AB from a large viewing tower right near the cabins. Other nights, we drove as far as Norway to see them, even stopping off the side of the road when the Borealis presented itself. At times it came and went quickly but when the activity was strong, we watched for 20-25 minutes at a time!

After being picked up from the airport (it‚Äôs about a 2+ hour drive up to the cabins), we were dropped off at a large grocery store to buy all the needed supplies for the week. We had 1 hour which is just enough to translate some Finnish product descriptions (outside the obvious fruits, veg, chips, etc).

Tony and team (Ian was really great, super helpful and also friendly and always made us feel so welcomed) offered activities on all days (the husky rides, ice-fishing, ice fall snow shoe walking, snowmobiling and reindeer farm visit) can be purchased √† la carte and paid same day. This means you can plan them relatively last minute and if you prefer to just walk around the forest or rest in the cabins you can.

The tours also provided full snowsuits and the snowshoes if you needed.

Lastly, there is a covered common smoke pit near the viewing tower where we grilled artic fish one night, we saw our neighbors making smores and other foods too.

We had a great experience and would recommend them to anyone planning a trip up to see the Aurora Borealis!

During my last moments in Frankfurt, since my ticket was delayed, I had to quickly book a hotel.
First of all, I‚Äôm really thankful for the Agoda app‚Äîit makes searching with filters so easy and offers great deals.
This hotel was one of their recommendations.

I asked around about safety, and apparently, it‚Äôs not recommended to walk around that area after midnight.
But I absolutely loved the location‚Äîit gave me easy access to everywhere and everything was nearby.
My room was so clean, spacious, and nice.

I honestly think everything was perfect.
I didn‚Äôt have time to interact much with the staff, but even with the limited contact, they were very helpful and kind.
I was satisfied with everything, and if I go to Frankfurt again, I‚Äôll definitely choose this place.
Oh, and their prices are amazing!

The only downside was that I could hear noise coming from the neighboring room.
There was a locked door connecting the two rooms, and I really wish there had been a wall instead of a door‚Äîit would have made things much better.

Last but not least, the staff was super friendly and helpful ‚Äî great service all around!

Highly recommended if you're looking for a great shisha experience in a stylish and welcoming environment.

Location is great, apartment is clean and well equipped with towels and dishes.
However, the noise is unbearable, some club/restaurant is in front of the building, there is music and loud people all night long. The Wi-Fi hasn‚Äôt been working even for a second during our stay. They said they were trying to fix it, but we sincerely doubt it. If you are there for short stay, and don‚Äôt mind not sleeping well for couple of nights, recommend it just for location and cleanliness. Also, if you are planning to cook something, bear in mind there is no salt, pepper, oil in the apartment, just coffee pods and sugar.

name: Aura Luxury Apartments
description:
Dear Manolis and Aura Luxury Apartments team,

I want to express my deepest gratitude for the unforgettable stay at your wonderful property in Ierissos. The studio we booked was absolutely amazing ‚Äì beautifully furnished, brand new, and spotless. It made our family vacation so much more special. Ierissos itself is such a beautiful place, with excellent restaurants and stunning beaches that made our trip even more enjoyable!

A special thank you to Manolis ‚Äì you are truly the best host! When we were leaving for Sofia, we had a problem with the car key and couldn‚Äôt start the engine. Manolis spent the entire day helping us, even calling his friends to try to fix the issue. It got very late, and despite everything, he took us and our luggage back to the studio and allowed us to stay overnight free of charge. We can‚Äôt find words to express our gratitude to him and his friends for going above and beyond to help us in every possible way.

Manolis, if you ever read this, know that we will always remember your kindness! Wishing you and your family all the best, and I truly hope we can meet again this summer!

Warm regards,
Galina Goranova

name: Aura Luxury Suites
description:
I had a very pleasant stay here. The property is newly built in a modern style, with a lot of taste.
The location is excellent ‚Äî close to the town center, yet peaceful, and near the forest and hills.
There is plenty of parking space.
Everything is clean and well-maintained, and the staff is very friendly.
The entire place is built with quality, using modern and high-end materials.
The courtyard is nicely arranged and spotless.

name: Aura Suites Paros
description:
We recently stayed at this incredible hotel in Paros with our two small children, and we can confidently say it was the best hotel experience we‚Äôve ever had.

From the moment we arrived, we were welcomed with warmth and genuine hospitality. The location is ideal ‚Äì peaceful and picturesque, yet just minutes from all the charm and attractions of Paros. It‚Äôs the perfect balance of relaxation and convenience.

Our room was spotless, spacious, and beautifully designed ‚Äì truly a haven after a day of exploring. Traveling with kids can be challenging, but the comfort and cleanliness of the room made everything so much easier and more enjoyable.

What really set this stay apart was the outstanding service. A special shoutout to Antonia, Niko and the entire staff, who went above and beyond to make sure we were comfortable, cared for, and completely at home. Their kindness toward our children was especially touching ‚Äì from thoughtful gestures to warm smiles, they made our whole family feel truly welcomed.

Every detail, from the service to the setting, was perfection. We left with full hearts, happy memories, and a strong desire to return. If you‚Äôre traveling to Paros - don‚Äôt think twice. This is the place to stay.

name: Aura Villa Mykonos
description: A truly lovely villa. A bit too far from things. A chair broke on me while we were eating dinner, the first night that had to be paid for in full and was requested before our stay was even up. Mentioning this because I feel the chair had been broken before and glued back (so watch out), thus it breaking on me. The host was okay with negotiating the amount we would have to pay for it but honestly the whole Thing really took away from the overall trip. I am of average weight and did not feel comfortable sitting on anything that was not concrete which is no way to vacation.

name: Hajnal √âp√≠t√©sziroda Kft.
description: They don't respond to letters or official inquiries, they prefer to hide. Frivolous. The negative evaluation is reported rather than answered!

name: Hajnal Beauty Relax - Kozmetika
description:
I've been going to Hajni for almost a year and a half to get my soul in order, and my face gets the right treatment too :)
I look forward to the treatments every time, whether it's for my soul or my face... Hajni works wonders for me.. every time I'm there and she applies all sorts of amazing stuff to my face, I'm surrounded by a calm atmosphere that lasts even after the treatment: even when I step out onto the bustling street, I feel like I'm in the same bubble that surrounded me in the salon.
I wholeheartedly recommend Hajni to everyone who believes that beautiful skin and a well-groomed soul belong together

name: Aura Budapest Perfumery
description: Absolutely stunning store with a high-end, luxurious vibe! The staff is super knowledgeable and friendly, I‚Äôm in love with the scent I chose, and it lasts forever!!

name: Aurea Ana Palace Hotel
description:
We stayed here for three nights.

Pros -
Good location
Nice interior though not sure about the giant portrait of Sisi watching me sleep‚Ä¶
Room was clean
Bathroom was modern
Late night cocktails are good

Cons -
Room AC is loud and difficult to get the room to a good temperature.
Service is horrible for supposedly a 5 star hotel:
No one greets you at the entrance
No help with bags
No concierge
No clarity on Spa rules, some people walking around naked, some with bathing suits. No member of staff at the Spa desk.
Price of all minibar is basically the cost of a night at the hotel.

The room service menu doesn‚Äôt have any descriptions of the items so I called and asked what was in the ‚ÄúClub Sandwich‚Äù, the person on the other end of the phone did not know and suggested I go down to the bar to find out‚Ä¶ I then requested they find out and call back. They did not call back.

Staff are just generally untrained and lack the experience to deliver what is required for 5 star. The hotel generally is nice but it lacks finesse and refinement that you normally expect at this price point. I will never come back nor would I stay at any of their group hotels.

The manager offered to comp our last breakfast (‚Ç¨25) and hotel transfer (‚Ç¨50) in response to the above which was a nice gesture.

description: Cute museum about how the aurora borealis is formed. They had nice viewing areas to watch the different auroras that have been filmed over Iceland. The gift shop was really cute. You could buy and send postcards from there as well!

name: Aurora Experts - Iceland
description: As someone who‚Äôs chased Aurora right around the world, from Alaska to Norway, Iceland to Canada, I‚Äôve seen my fair share of Northern lights tour operators. Heimer is by far and away the best guide I‚Äôve had the pleasure of chasing with. His tour combines his passion for the northern lights and his willingness to find clear skies for his guests. I joined Heimer over 2 nights in Feb 2025, and I can‚Äôt recommend him higher to those looking for a quality northern lights tour. The tour also includes food & drink that incorporates traditional Icelandic food. He‚Äôs a down to earth person who puts his heart on the line for his job and he offered me a free tour after a roaring success in helping him watching the data as he drove. He‚Äôs not a guide that drives you to a certain spot, he actively monitors the weather and solar data to give his guests the best chance at seeing the northern lights and is an absolute wizard behind the camera for all your Aurora portrait needs. 5 stars from me and wouldn‚Äôt go with anyone else!!!

I highly recommend if you‚Äôre looking for more unique experiences

name: Aurora Forecast Iceland

The hotel restaurant is very good although might come as a sticker shock to some, but it is Iceland and the only hotel close to the airport. There‚Äôs no other restaurants nearby unless you want to eat at the airport. I would have to say that breakfast buffet was included in our stay and that was worthwhile

name: Auralia
description:
Exceptional Care & Outstanding Results

From my very first consultation to my final follow-up, I felt completely supported, informed, and cared for at Auralia . My surgeon took the time to listen to my concerns, answer every question with patience, and guide me toward the right choice for my body and goals.

The entire team‚Äôs professionalism, kindness, and attention to detail made me feel safe and confident throughout the process. On surgery day, everything ran smoothly, and I was reassured every step of the way. Post-op care was equally exceptional ‚Äî I never felt rushed or dismissed, and any concerns I had were addressed immediately.

I‚Äôm thrilled with my results and so grateful for the genuine care and skill that went into my treatment. I wouldn‚Äôt hesitate to recommend this surgeon to anyone considering a procedure ‚Äî you‚Äôll be in the very best hands.

name: Chakra By Jaipur
description: Took my team for dinner here. One of our colleagues recommended this place. We had reservations so we were seated right away. Food was delicious. Service was excellent. They had Himalayan Goat on limited time menu which was perfect in terms of flavors. Paneer was probably second best. Everything from appetizers to main course was great. Highly recommend this place if you want to taste Indian food with blend of flavors. Some Indian restaurants will add overwhelming amount of spices but this place has best balance of ingredients so you can taste distinct flavors. It‚Äôs a Michelin recommended restaurant.

name: Dervish Crystal and Holistic Shop Dublin
description: I absolutely loved this shop! It is a hidden gem for anyone interested in esoteric items like tarot cards, crystals, and more. The staff is knowledgeable and friendly, always willing to help you find what you‚Äôre looking for. The selection of esoteric items is truly impressive, and I‚Äôve found some unique treasures here!

name: Aurora Print & Display
description: Polite and quick service. Affordable as well. Very kind extra gestures really appreciated. Definitely recommend their services.

name: Aurora Studios
description:
Jamie, the locket arrived already today!! Which meant I was able to gift it to our childminder today, at the end of her last day with us. There were a lot of tears!!!

The inscription and the photos in the locket were just perfect, and it was such a beautiful piece of jewellery. I'm really so grateful, the quality is outstanding, delivery unbelievably fast, and you've created something for us which is really a keepsake for life.

Thank you. Amazing business you're running.

name: Aurora Telecom
description: Terrible - stay well clear.  They currently supply phone and internet to our business in London. Internet connect is slow and grinds to a holt frequently around 3pm daily.  Phone line is currently down  have to wait 48hrs to find out when an engineer can come out.

name: Aura Internet Services Ltd
description: A great company to work with, they are professional, creative and are always willing to go the extra mile for you. They are passionate, hardworking and guide you seamlessly through your project whether it be development, design or training.  Overall, it's was a great experience to work with Aura Internet.

name: Aura Drogheda Leisure Centre
description:
I visited Aura today, and I found the experience to be absolutely despicable and disastrous. Shockingly, they allowed a woman to enter the swimming pool in the WATER fully clothed, including wearing a veil. Even more concerning, the man accompanying her presumably the husband was also fully dressed in regular clothes and did not respect the rules of the swimming pool.

This raises serious concerns about hygiene standards. What kind of policy does the swimming facility have in place regarding appropriate swimwear and sanitation? Such practices are not only unhygienic but also reflect poorly on the management‚Äôs commitment to public health and safety for EVERYONE!

name: Aura Tullamore Leisure Centre
description:
So, the reason I gave this review 2 stars and not 1 is because the staff are always quite nice at reception and help if anything is needed.

The issues in Aura tullamore are more about the maintenance in the gym locker rooms (male and female).

The showers have chipped tiles, the lockers don't have any straps on any of the keys, and I can't even begin to describe the  toilet in the changing area. I've seen cleaner toilets at music festivals. They seem to be cleaned maybe once every day and there is hardly ever toilet paper.

The drains always smell quite badly, the tiles are covered in snot, chewing gum, and are cleaned very infrequently (i believe based on condition).

If you compare this to other facilities in the court hotel, or snap fitness they are far worse in terms of the changing facilities they have and also the cleanliness standards.

They also recently changed policy and my teenage son can't go post 6.30 which has limited his ability to train (he is a competitive swimmer and used to train evenings at the gym)

All in all since i rejoined this year (i was a member a long time ago) I'm far more inclined to go back to the court hotel or snap fitness due to everything described.

Just to reiterate, the staff are great. This isn't a staff issue, it's a facilities and hygiene issue.

name: Aura Dundalk Leisure Centre
description:
On a positive note, the staff are always very friendly at the reception. The swimming lessons and swim teachers are also excellent.

Now the negatives. The gym locker rooms are a disgrace. There is always rubbish on the floor and in the lockers. The toilets and shower areas are also filthy. It's very off-putting, especially considering it's not particularly cheap in comparison to other gyms around the town, despite being council owned.

name: Aura Youghal Leisure Centre
description:
Brought my kids for the specific purpose of using the slide. Paid in with no mention of slide being closed for most of the session. Changing area/showers are filthy. Sand in the pools. Totally inadequate showers for the number of people.
Kids got 2 goes on the slide with the excuse there's not enough staff. Apparently there are no plans to hire more or change this in any way, yet still charge full price for use.

name: Aura Leitrim Leisure Centre
description:
the gym and the pool are good, and the new equipment for the gym has become much better, but it seems like more exercise machines are needed, which are not there, but the aura is a good sports complex)
the staff is always friendly,so i can't give it too low a rating because aura is a good sports complex but i think there is some work to do

One star less due to toilets, sometimes they are not clean. Other than that, very nice place to swim.

Recommend especially for people with kids, but even for just adults who want to swim is a great place.

üåüüåüüåüüåüüåü

description:
What a wonderful bar!!!
This is the perfect spot to relax and unwind after your Vatican tour, whether you‚Äôre in the mood for a spritz, an iced coffee, a sandwich, or some gelato. The space is clean, welcoming, and well-equipped with everything you might need. The staff speaks excellent English, along with several other languages. It‚Äôs rare to find such outstanding service in Rome, but this bar truly delivers. 5/5!

name: Casino dell'Aurora di Villa Ludovisi Boncompagni
description: If you get the chance to visit and see Caravaggio‚Äôs only ceiling painting it is well worth it‚Äîyou get some bonus Guerchino frescoes as well, and the house as well as the history behind it is fascinating like so many things in Roma! I was able to see the house thanks to the Caravaggio 2025 show, who knows when it will be open again so take the opportunity if it arises!

name: Aurora Penne Boutique
description:
I was sightseeing in Rome when I found this Aurora Boutique. Being a customer (and a fan) of the brand, I had to go inside and see the available products.

Ms Liana provided top-class service, letting me try various pens before making a purchase and going the extra mile to ensure I got the model more adequate to my needs.

Next time I am in Rome, I will be sure to stop by, and I recommend purchasing at this store for any fountain pen enthusiast, Roman or otherwise, who would like to get to know Aurora better!

name: Angolo Dell'Aurora
description: I visited the restaurant during evening hours, slightly before dinner. I went with my family (husband and 2kids). We had an amazing time. The food was the best we tried in Italy, the service was top notch (very beautiful and kind server). I ate the home made pasta with tomato Sauce and sausages, it was amazing, my kids had lasagna and pizza (they costumed our order) and it was very good too. After the meal, the pianist was entertaining our kids with such beautiful Italy songs and some classic ones. Definitely a must visit if you are in Rome in the vicinity!

name: Aurora 31 Suite & Bed and Breakfast Rome
description:
Pros: They were flexible with our check-in time, it was clean, close to the Borghese Gallery, and the lady who checked us in was very friendly.
Cons: it was not as advertised. The air conditioning did not work (it was nearly 100 degrees Fahrenheit during our stay), and when I mentioned the heat to the lady who checked us in, she simply pointed to a single fan on the floor. The bed was wooden boards topped by a thin mattress topper. The "terrace" was a window with an old wreath hanging on it. Breakfast was a broken coffee pot and a stale, dry waffle packaged on a shelf. Toiletries were a collection of open, used various items left behind by previous guests.

name: Villa Aurora
description:
The villa has been in the media as it has been on sale for several years. The price is said to be at several hundred millions.

There are only three rooms open to tourists, for which tickets are booked in advance with a guided tour only.
These rooms are Very authentic and have beautiful ceiling paintings by Guercino .
However , the visit is overpriced as Euro 25.00  is a lot to see only 3 rooms. The famous frescoe by Caravaggio cannot be seen, neither the first floor or the famous staircase.
The entry to the villa is very discrete.

name: Aurora Penne
description:
Deeply dishonest company. They marketed and sold a pen called the Aurora Optima Nebulosa as a North American exclusive and limited edition less than two years before they rereleased it as a regular edition worldwide for substantially less.

Their social media manager lies through their teeth on their Instagram page when questioned about it. If you post proof to the contrary they just delete it and ban you. Whoever is in charge over there can't even Google basic info on the pens they're supposed to be selling or ask Aurora directly for the correct information.

Reselling a limited edition as a regular edition breaks consumer protection laws in both New York State and Illinois. There are likely other states where this is considered illegal as well since each state has its own laws.

Gorgeous pens but the company's tactics are scummy unfortunately. I bought four of them previously and used one to sign my wedding certificate but Aurora's blatant lies have killed my desire to ever buy another.

Plenty of other pen makers out there who won't lie to your face to make a sale.

Compliments

name: Aura Organic Spa
description: Aura Spa is a local hidden gem! The staff are friendly and welcoming, and the facial services are absolutely outstanding. You leave feeling refreshed, pampered, and glowing. Highly recommend! üíÜ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüå∏

name: Aura Group Srl

name: Aura Graph
description: highly trained and helpful staff...An excellence of our territory..Highly recommended.

name: Restaurant Auras
description:
We had dinner at Auras on our last night in Ischia and the experience and the food did not disappoint.
We had reservations so the table was ready when we arrived.  Julio was our main server and he was so friendly and did an amazing job taking care of us the whole evening.
We chose this restaurant because it had a lot of vegetarian options.  He made sure to understand our dietary needs and then he made some great recommendations.
They brought us some bread with an amazing olive oil to enjoy with our drinks while we soaked in the view of the castle that looms tall in the landscape.
The food came out and was so so delicious!  I highly recommend the squash blossoms.  All the food was amazing honestly.
It was a 10/10 on atmosphere and overall experience and a 10/10 on the food itself.  I highly recommend this place if you are in Ischia‚Ä¶if you get Julio as the server that‚Äôs just a bonus!
Pro tip:  don‚Äôt skip the French fries!!!!!

name: Euronics
description: We didn‚Äôt open the box during the collection in the shop and got the microwave like this. By the way they delivered the fridge with scratches as well. 95% of the stuff are very unfriendly.

name: Old Wild West
description:
Service was just a huge disappointment. Some of the staff had this condescending vibe that made me feel silly for even asking questions. I overheard another customer who was visibly frustrated because their food came out cold. When they mentioned it to the staff, it was like they were met with a wall of indifference. name: The Westin Dragonara Resort, Malta
description:
Reviewing the Reef club only‚Ä¶ Beautiful location, but staff communication really lets it down.
I spent a day at The Reef Club using a day pass, and while the setting is undeniably beautiful, the experience was let down by poor communication and indifferent staff.

The location itself is lovely ‚Äî clear water (a bit choppy as it‚Äôs open sea, not a bay), and there are little pockets of calm, including a sandy cove that‚Äôs great for swimming. There are plenty of sunbeds spread out across the club, so finding a quiet space to relax is easy, and the vibe is peaceful and scenic.

However, the staff really let the experience down.
When I arrived, I paid ‚Ç¨45 at reception and was given no information at all ‚Äî I only found out later (by asking) that there was a ‚Ç¨65 option that included food vouchers. That was never mentioned to me. When I asked for a towel, I was told bluntly that they don‚Äôt provide towels ‚Äî which honestly feels a bit absurd for a five-star hotel beach club charging premium rates. I did manage to get one eventually from a kind staff member, but the tone was not welcoming.

Beyond that, there was zero guidance:
‚Ä¢	No explanation of which areas I could access
‚Ä¢	No directions to the bar, restrooms, or restaurant
‚Ä¢	No schedule or info about service times
I was just vaguely gestured toward the sunbeds and left to figure it all out myself.

I made the best of it ‚Äî had a good swim, relaxed, enjoyed a cocktail ‚Äî but when I tried to order food a bit later, I found out the kitchen had closed at 3:30 PM. Again, no one told me this at any point. If I had known, I would‚Äôve ordered lunch earlier.

It‚Äôs a real shame, because the physical space has a lot of potential and I still enjoyed my time there. But the lack of hospitality and basic service standards really made it feel like I was more of a nuisance than a guest.

name: Wandering Owl
description:
We went on the Adults Only Aurora Hunt. This was one of five hunts we went on, with four different service providers, and it was our clear favorite.

You receive an email after booking,  telling you to be at the Ishavhotel prior to your departure time. Our hunt occurred on our second day in the city, and we were still a little unfamiliar with everything. We got to the hotel early. There were a few people standing around for other tours, but there was no signage there or tour representatives. Eventually there were a lot of people there and mini buses started showing up later. Suddenly guides started calling out names of their group. We were starting to worry there was a problem with our booking, but our names were finally called several groups later. This initial meeting seemed a bit chaotic, but the same process was used by three of the four tour providers, though one of them had a marked minibus that made it easy to spot.

There were only six of us in our group, so our minibus had plenty of room and was comfortable. Unfortunately, as the temperature dropped later in the hunt, the side door quit working; so, we had to lay back the driver's seat and climb in and out over it to get in and out of the minibus.

Our guide, Tomas, immediately explained the plan for the evening as we left Tromso. He was very engaging throughout the evening.  We discussed the science of the aurora, and he also told us about the native Sami culture. All of it was interesting. He was the second oldest of our five different guides.
He was mature and professional, but also very upbeat and excited about us seeing the aurora.

We drove three hours to the Finnish - Swedish border, near Keinovuopio, Sweden. We stopped once at a small store where snacks and toilets were available. We stopped again somewhere near Skibotin, Norway, where we saw a beautiful aurora display! Tomas took photos of the group and the aurora. He easily could have called it night, having seen the lights, but we drove on to the Keinovuopio area, where we set up for the rest of the evening. We were once again treated with a beautiful aurora show! Both spots were very picturesque!

The hunt included tripods, help with camera settings, a warm fire, food and drink, and warm clothing. Everyone in our group had their own photography equipment and there wasn't much discussion about settings. I feel certain assistance would have been given, if requested. The soup was rather bland, but it was hot and was fine for the circumstances. My wife used the provided boots and found them to be much warmer than her own. It was also nice that folding chairs were available for sitting by the fire later in the evening! The tour also included free web-size resolution photos and original resolution size photos were available for purchase. We purchased three of the higher resolution photos and received a separate link for downloading them. This link was only good for seven days. It would have been nice for the link to last longer, as we traveled for another three weeks. I would have liked to download the higher resolution photos directly to my home desktop computer.

After a long, enjoyable evening we packed up and headed back to Tromso, where we were dropped off at our hotel.

Despite the small issues discussed above, we found this to be an extremely enjoyable tour. We could not have had a better guide than Tomas! We're considering returning to Tromso for the next aurora season and will definitely book with Wondering Owl again!

name: Luna Hotel da Oura
description:
The Worst Stay of My Life ‚Äì Avoid at All Costs!

Where do I even begin? From the moment I stepped into this excuse of a hotel, I was met with nothing but rudeness and indifference. The front desk staff acted like I was an inconvenience rather than a paying guest. No greetings, no smiles‚Äîjust eye rolls and clipped answers like they were doing me a favor by checking me in.

Things only went downhill from there.

No air conditioning. In the middle of a heatwave, mind you. I was told, ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs an old building,‚Äù as if that somehow excused them from providing a basic necessity. The room was a sauna, and when I asked for a fan, they shrugged and said, ‚ÄúWe might have one. Try again later.‚Äù

Speaking of ‚Äúold building,‚Äù that seems to be their excuse for everything. The appliances in the room looked like they were stolen from a thrift store in the 1980s and haven‚Äôt been cleaned since. The mini-fridge rattled like it was possessed, the microwave was missing half the buttons, and the TV only picked up static and despair.

The overall condition of the room? Grimy. Stained carpets, peeling wallpaper, and a bathroom that smelled faintly of mildew and stronger of regret.

Don‚Äôt be fooled by any filtered photos or half-hearted responses from management. This place is a rundown disaster run by people who clearly don‚Äôt care. I wouldn‚Äôt stay here again if it were free‚Äîand frankly, they should be paying guests to stay.

Zero stars if I could. You‚Äôve been warned.

One bartender, Diego, was unbelievably rude. I had to speak to management at reception. They said they will look into it, but I am not sure anything will happen.

I can accept simple food or old rooms, but not bad attitude from staff. If someone doesn‚Äôt want to do their job, maybe this is not the right place for them.

Her Arnica salve has been a companion for a while now - I use it for everything from joint & muscle pain to treating burns and cuts and I‚Äôm never not amazed at the effectiveness of this magical plant creation.
The same magic is to be found in her Aloe Vera balm, as I‚Äôm sure it is in all other products. I recently used the Aloe salve for a mild sunburn and was quite stunned by how quickly it relieved the redness.

Gratitude to you for the beautiful work you do, dear Juju!

Even the jets from the wirlpool dindt work. Some walls have mold and in the front gardent of property you find old tires. There is a extra fee for sauna, dog , grill and electricity- witch isnt clearly written in booking.com site. You need to tell them in advance if you want to use it, wich isnt written nowhere. The wood for the fireplace was wet and the chimney jammed - so smoke everywhere. The gas grill was low on gas and not powerfull at all (- we had no gas in the end ). We had paddle boards for the kids under supervision of adults. It wasnt written anywhere they are not allowed. Even we where only 12 adults, the owner was sure, he counted on cameras 20 people - wich isnt true. The swimming pool supposed the have 28-29c , we measured with thermometer and it was freezing 22c. We asked several times how big the cooking station ist for gulas, the answer is its for about 3kg meat - for about 15Liters soup. The tennis court was by the way also in bad shape - the net was falling apart. The rooms were clean and good.After 3 days of stay we were asked to pay 120‚Ç¨ for the dog, sauna and electricity - just that others know.
