name: CopaCabana Aribau
description: Ok, so we chose the place because we found a 50% discount and the photos didn't look bad. When we get there the ambiance is a full discotec or club. So first thing to notice, this was a club, and 2 months ago it also became a restaurant. So chairs, tables, look of the place and distributions were not good at all. Impressive at first because of the amount of space but as you stop and see details... It gets disappointing. Like for example a hole in a chair that was patched with black tape. The entrance is a long long bar that is completely alone... Kind of unsettling. From the start you feel a little bit weird. We pass the long bar/hallway entrance and we are greeted (will have loved to be greeted at the real entrance) by Jose Maria, who says it's the manager of the place, he was really chatty but with overall good attitude, a little bit to much into jokes but it was ok. We sit at the table and he keeps chatting, my friend (I was with my girlfriend and my friend who is visiting Barcelona) has little patience and cuts Jose right away and says "Jose what about a beer first" it was a bit rude from my friend part but you first need to make people confortable and then chat a lot, sorry for that Jose Maria. We asked for 3 beers, coronas, after asking us if we wanted lime with them we were then told that the coronas were not cold and that he could get us Budweiser (the manager didn't know what they have and what they didn't) ... I said no thanks, don't like watery beer. Jose Maria made us 3 cocktails so we could have something to drink, courtesy of the house, that was good, it shows they care about clients, but the cocktail was not really good at all besides being poorly presented... Non of us finished it, my friend ended up getting the Budweiser, my girl water, and I asked for a Cuba libre... Jose Maria was the manager, waiter and also the bartender, there was another bartender/waiter that was also a bouncer, they were really understaffed. At this point I had to teach Jose Maria how to make a Cuba libre... Which was fun but not what you expect from a restaurant or even bar... Later my girlfriend went to the bathroom and as she came back she said one of the toilets smelled horrible and had a lot of flies.... Then the food came... This is when I got mad, the food was barely eatable and not what you see in the photos, nothing was well thought or prepared, meat was processed (toro and cochinillo) and looked like you took it out of the fridge and put it in the microwave... Even with the 50% discount the food was not worth it... No plate was lower than 20‚Ç¨.. With the 50% discount they range from 10-13‚Ç¨... I wouldn't pay more than 5‚Ç¨ for what I was served... Please consider you can go to a normal michellin restaurant and one plate can cost you between 20-30‚Ç¨... This place is selling poorly prepared dishes for 26‚Ç¨... The place is really dark so when you see the dishes in the photos they look better than what they are. Also they have their own photos which don't represent at all the quality of food that we got served... I was open minded and friendly till the food arrived, that's when my face changed, we eat a little bit and asked for the bill right away, 60‚Ç¨ thrown away in my opinion. Jose Maria wasn't a bad host, but also not excellent, I assume it must be difficult if the place and food don't help. They told us that other days they have live music... Maybe this place is just good for drinks (beers, they don't have good bartenders, so I wouldn't recommend cocktails) and music... In conclusion Club that tries to be a restaurant in a fancy zone (above diagonal) and fails completely... Won't go there ever again... Waste of money, if you are hungry you are better off eating burgers or a kebad... That's how bad the quality of the food was here in relation to the price. As I was about to sleep I even got nausea which was alarming, if the bathroom was like that how was the kitchen?

I had a wax here and the spatula used was used throughout the whole wax then left back in the pot for which I imagine is the next client. Very unhygienic.

Double dipping in waxing refers to the unsanitary practice of re-dipping a used spatula or applicator back into the wax pot after it has been in contact with a client's skin. This can introduce bacteria, viruses, and other contaminants into the wax, potentially leading to infections or other health issues.

name: AURA
description:
The address is incorrect and has not been corrected (actual Titova 2)
Pros:
1) The area is well landscaped, everything is in flowers!
2) There are always available rooms (double room $20/night without meals)
Of the minuses:
1) Soviet service in its entirety (service from the position of ‚Äúwhere are you going‚Äù)
2) A working refrigerator with freezer was found in only one of the five rooms offered
3) A broken toilet seat (they replaced it ‚Äúsmacking their lips displeasedly‚Äù with a whole one, but even the whole one was so uncomfortable that after leaving, my legs hurt for another 5 days)
4) The plumbing is all in a rusty and unsatisfactory condition (there is only cold water on the washbasins and no sprayer, the mixer in the shower was covered in machine oil, perhaps because of this, the water had an unpleasant smell, while we were looking for a room with a freezer, I saw a unique toilet tank: instead of a button there is a hole, with a rope sticking out of it with a ring that needs to be pulled!)
5) Single beds are put together and there is foam rubber between them, and the bed linen is only single bed linen - no matter how you sleep, it still lies on the seam, but the truth is you don‚Äôt feel it compared to faulty springs in the mattress
6) Meals are provided only in the base canteen, although they said on the phone that there is a shared kitchen. And there are no cutlery sets in the rooms; they are given the bare minimum, ‚Äúsmacking their lips displeasedly‚Äù: a spoon, a fork, a small plate, a cup, and only on request. There is a shared kitchen in the gazebo, but with one gas stove (when the wind blows out the fire) with four burners. In the common kitchen there are no utensils for cooking, i.e. there is nothing at all. Everyone is welcome! once you go to the dining room, look for the administrator Lyudmila Ivanovna and ask for a frying pan (without a handle!) or a saucepan (old Soviet aluminum). It‚Äôs better not to ask for a frying pan and a saucepan at the same time, so as not to hear a ‚Äúdissatisfied smacking‚Äù with the words ‚ÄúAre you going to cook borscht!?!‚Äù or ‚Äúcheaper than in our canteen, food is not possible!‚Äù
The prices in the dining room are greatly inflated; one complex for one will cost about $5. Thanks to the infrastructure of the area (a shop is a 2-minute walk away and a market is 5 minutes away), you can organize, on your own, five times a day! a complete balanced diet for two! person it turned out to be $5 a day! Additional expenses for food included the purchase of a personal frying pan for $7 and a saucepan for $10 in the center of Kirillovka (travel by minibus (every ten minutes) one way per person is $0.38), so as not to spoil your vacation by communicating with the dissatisfied administration.

I appreciated Thimela's suggestion to take a day or two off work following the session to maintain the relaxation and freshness attained. It was evident when I went to work the next day feeling a bit tired and drained. Following Thimela's advice on consuming good food, staying hydrated, avoiding sugar, and focusing on high-nutrient foods further contributed to sustaining the positive effects of the session.

In conclusion, my visit to Chakra Mama Healing with Thimela was truly transformative, and I would highly recommend it to anyone seeking a holistic healing experience. Thimela's expertise and guidance create a nurturing environment for relaxation and self-care. Thank you for a wonderful experience!

description:

When we finally reached the front, the same bouncer told us we should have paid him earlier. We explained we didn't have cash, and to that, he smugly replied that he also accepts Interac e-transfer. Again, we refused, and he became rude and dismissive, saying, "Then you must wait." At that point, we'd had enough and chose to leave and spend our night (and money) elsewhere.

To top it all off, the bouncer appeared jittery and erratic - honestly, he looked like he might have been under the influence of something. Not exactly the kind of person who should be representing your venue or deciding who gets in.

Absolutely unprofessional and shady behavior. Won't be returning, and I wouldn't recommend this place to anyone looking for a good night out.

name: Chakra Retreat Center
description: We had a wonderful 4 days at Chakra - it just wasn't long enough!  It's the most peaceful and relaxing place i've been.  It's off grid and very rustic with no wifi so you have to switch off and watch the birds.  The food was delicious, there's a beautiful river to have dip and our guide, Ursula, made us feel comfortable and well looked after at all times. We tried abseiling and tree climbing, hiked up Cerro Ena, spent lots of time relaxing in a hammock, did yoga and visited a local coffee farmer - all were wonderful.  I hope to visit again one day.

The location is amazing: close to Roseau without the city noise and a short driving distance to Trafalgar Falls, hot springs, Titou Gorge and Boiling Lake trailhead. The host, Ginette, provided everything we needed for our stay.  We were happily surprised she provided things we forgot to pack: sunscreen, aftersun lotion, bug spray & floss.  She provides great recommendations for attractions and can set up tours.  Very strong wifi.  We came to Ginette's property after having a poor signal at another property and were very happy we made the change!

name: Aura Beach Club Cabarete
description:
I went there with my wife and baby twice during my stay in Cabarete. First time was for cocktails and an appetizer. The cocktails were excellent and appetizer was very good.   The second time we went for lunch and some cocktails. The food was excellent as well as the cocktails.
The beach restaurant is rather new to Cabarete and is a great addition to the beach scene.  The place elegantly decorated and comfortable. Probably, the nicest place on the beach right now. Great for a birthday or an anniversary.
The view of the beach is spectacular.
The service was great. The waiter was attentive and professional.
I hope Aura keeps going with their high standards.

An excellent place to purchase electric transportation. I purchased a very nice-looking scooter with great range, good tires, lights, and disc brakes. Victor's service was top-notch. I previously took a test drive, and everything went as expected.
I wish them success and hope more people learn about them and purchase their products. They are an example of how it's not just about selling, but also about satisfying people with first-class service.

name: Silversands Grand Anse
description: We just returned from a week at this resort, and it was by far the best resort experience I‚Äôve had in Grenada.  Based on previous experiences at other resorts on the island, I was worried about rude staff ruining my stay, But ALL the team members I‚Äôve encountered at Silversands were warm, friendly, attentive and engaging. We were celebrating our anniversary, and our awesome experience began BEFORE we arrived.  The reservation process was seamless, and when we arrived, there were a bottle of champagne and chocolate in our room.  What a nice touch!!  Also, the resort is quite beautiful! The room was large, airy and sun-filled, with a view of the beach. The bathroom is large, and the bed and pillows were so comfortable. Can‚Äôt wait to return! The only negative is the food and drinks‚Ä¶which were expensive for their quality and quantity. There are better options within walking distance of the resort. Nevertheless, Silversands gets a 5 star because in a nutshell, it is an exceptional resort.

name: Silversands Beach House
description: The beach house is a phenomenal resort!! We‚Äôve been to island vacations all over the world and this is by far our favorite. The rooms, views, services and staff are all top notch. The staff really make it welcoming and fun because they are truly kind and funny and always remember us. Going to the spa at the sister property on Grand Anse was heavily. I was completely pampered. I would recommend this place to anyone who wants the best beach vacation of their lives.

name: Aura Anse-Marcel
description:
A Truly Exceptional Stay at Aura Hotel

My stay at the Aura Hotel was absolutely fantastic. From the moment I arrived, I was blown away by the beauty of the property and the breathtaking views. The location is truly stunning ‚Äî peaceful, picturesque, and perfect for a relaxing getaway.

One of the highlights of my experience was the outstanding service provided by my concierge, Yann. He was incredibly accommodating and friendly, assisting with bookings and ensuring every detail of my stay went smoothly. His hospitality really made a lasting impression.

As a traveler from the U.S., I appreciated how seamless everything was ‚Äî I had no issues with currency exchange, which made things even more convenient. The villa service was flawless, offering both comfort and luxury.

I can‚Äôt emphasize enough how beautiful the setting was. Aura went above and beyond to make sure I felt welcome and taken care of. Without a doubt, I‚Äôll be returning. Highly recommended for anyone looking for an unforgettable stay.

name: Camper & Nicholsons Port Louis Marina
description: The best marina in the caribbean  !!  Employees are helpful and professional.  Fun activities,  and a great farmers market.  New swimming pool... what's not to Love !!

name: Chez Louis
description: The ambience and service were amazing. I would definitely visit again for that part. The drinks were fine as well, however the food was very disappointing and the portions wasn‚Äôt worth it. We ordered the calamari and it was too hard and dry that we could not finish it. I ordered the shrimp salad since I was feeling for something light, but I‚Äôm not certain what exactly it was about the shrimp, it had a very weird taste to it, and the sauce on the lettuce wasn‚Äôt doing it for me. My boyfriend had the shrimp orzo and it was the same thing for him. We can only base it on our experience and that was it. The staff were absolutely fantastic and everything else was fine but the food was a huge no, for the price at that.

name: Spice Harmony Yoga Studio
description: Malaika is an amazing yoga instructor and yoga therapist! And use of the yoga wall is a completely novel experience that is a true rare gem! The beautiful setting of studio and amazing view of the property are just added bonuses! This family run yoga studio sets a bar above the rest!

name: The Grenada Enterprises Group
description: Customer Service top notch! üëå.   An experience I will share. Variety of tiles and furniture. Quality at last, that lasts!

name: Andall & Associates Inc.
description: The red skinned female employee who serves food on Saturdays is very rude. I came there one Saturday in May and the lunches were not there. I asked her how long till it reaches she ignored me. I decided to wait and finally it came. I was the FIRST in the line. This lady just started to serve the girl from the back of me. I couldn't believe it. I stood there for about 5 minutes to see what she was all about and mind you she saw I was standing there... She began serving everyone to the back of me... While it is not the first time she ever served me, I also noticed there is an older guy with glasses, she serves very big and often do not place everything he orders on the box to be charged. I noticed this between these two on multiple occasions, But that Saturday was the last for me, will never purchase from there again

name: NOVARA DESIGN & CONSTRUCTION LTD
description: It's a construction and design group, specializing in engineering and architecture projects. Their staff is stellar!

name: Six Senses La Sagesse Grenada
description:
Our honeymoon at Six Senses Grenada was an absolute dream from start to finish. The resort is stunning, luxurious yet welcoming, and the attention to detail is unmatched. The staff went above and beyond to make us feel special and cared for every single day.

Having our own private pool with a breathtaking ocean view was a major highlight. It made the experience feel even more peaceful, romantic, and indulgent.

The food was also incredible - fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented at every meal. We especially appreciated how safe and relaxed we felt throughout our stay, allowing us to fully enjoy the serene, romantic atmosphere.

If you're looking for a truly unforgettable, high-end experience with top-notch service, delicious dining, and a stunning setting, Six Senses Grenada is it!

name: Akasha Metaphysical Shop
description:
Fell in love with this beautiful space as soon as I walked in the door.
The energy is so peaceful and calm. I took my family here for breakfast and we were all pleased with the food and service. The staff even went out of their way to go get tofu for our order as they had run out and gave us fresh fruit and breadfruit chips while we waited. The service was the best we have seen in Grenada.

The items available in the store include books, yoga mats, singing bowls, candles, supplements, loooots of stones and crystals and so much more.
Great place to find a unique gift for a special person.
I never imagined I'd find such a place in Grenada. ‚ù§Ô∏è

name: Aura
description: The villa's office warehouse is quite tidy and safe.

name: Aura Galer√≠as | Guatemala
description: Aura Galer√≠as is the best! They have art by very diverse and cosmopolitan artists! They give us the opportunity to discover and acquire works by foreign artists and, above all, they give us the peace of mind of knowing that they are original pieces! Their service is üîù! Bravo, Aura Galer√≠as!

name: La Aurora International Airport
description:
It's a pretty decent airport. It's got clear signs for everything and nice giftshops.

It could be the time we were there, but getting through security took less than 15 minutes, which I have never experienced.

The ports also work here. I can't say the same thing for other airports.

Great experience going through here.

name: Aurora C Jewelry
description: I highly recommend this place for finding unique, high-quality jewelry. I'm very happy with my new rings, and the service was excellent.

name: L‚ÄôAurora Inn
description:
We stayed here for a quick overnight before an early flight, and while the room was nice, our morning experience was a disaster. When I turned on the shower to warm up, it suddenly started spraying water everywhere. I understand that things like this can happen, but the way the situation was handled was completely unprofessional.

Instead of simply moving us to another room so we could get ready, they sent multiple people in and out of our room to try to fix it‚Äîwhile my husband was still inside trying to get dressed. I told them I needed to shower, and their solution was to offer me a dirty room instead. On top of that, while my husband was trying to eat the breakfast they had delivered, he had to keep moving so workers could pass by for the repair.

This all happened at 6:30 AM, and we were checking out at 7:30 AM. The hotel easily could have waited to do the repairs after we left, but instead, they made our last hour there chaotic and stressful. To make matters worse, the breakfast was cold and overly salty, adding to the frustration.

A hotel stay is supposed to be about comfort and convenience‚Äîthis was neither. We won‚Äôt be staying here again.

name: Aurora Networks Guatemala
description: very nice

name: Aurora Express
description: I had one of the worst experiences ever at this place. I was only staying for one short night and booking at this place turned my whole trip into a nightmare. The host was unresponsive after the ‚Äúbusiness‚Äù hours I was supposed to check in at around 1am due to my flight being delayed, once in the area I tried to contact the host several times to ask for directions, they never responded to my calls or messages. This place is not easy to get to at night and once in the ‚Äúresidential area‚Äù it‚Äôs even harder to find the house, there is no parking, people have to park on the street. I finally found it at 2:30am and had to leave by 5:30am for work. My biggest concern with this place and the reason I‚Äôm leaving a review is that this place shares guest personal information (name, phone number, nationality, race, etc.) with random people in the area,  I found out that my personal information was shared with several people who came to hotel asking for this, I called the hotel and Natalie the host confirmed that she had shared my personal information with this people, huge security and safety violation, when I questioned her about the legal reasons for doing so she told me that she can do this without the guest permission in this country, which is not correct. I posted a review on Expedia and the hotel reported this. I contacted Expedia and file a formal complaint against this place for sharing guest personal information to anyone who comes to their door asking for it.

name: Handcrafts Market
description:
Maybe I am uncultured, but it seems like most shops sell the same stuff with even the same designs. There are a couple of shops with cool unique products.

The one thing I bought was a Guatemalan bag with a nice design. It looks very beautiful but after a few uses, the strap broke and I had to sew it back together. It was 20 USD so it was pretty expensive for what seemed like a tote bag.

I didn't have a really good experience here. But this is a beautiful place to look around.

name: Zool√≥gico La Aurora
description:
‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è

This is hands down the best zoo I have ever been to in my life, and I‚Äôve visited quite a few over the years. There is an incredible variety of animals and exhibits, and the layout makes it easy to explore everything at your own pace. The zoo is exceptionally clean and well-maintained, which really enhances the overall experience and shows how much they care about the animals and visitors alike.

One of the things I appreciated most was how well-organized everything was‚Äîmaps, signage, and pathways all made it simple to find your way around and ensure you don‚Äôt miss any highlights. There‚Äôs so much to do and see, from interactive exhibits to animal feedings and shows, making it a fantastic day out for families, friends, or even solo visitors.

I would definitely recommend setting aside at least 4 hours if you want to see everything comfortably and really enjoy the full experience. The staff was friendly and knowledgeable, always happy to answer questions or share interesting facts about the animals.

Overall, this zoo exceeded all my expectations. It‚Äôs a perfect destination for anyone looking for a fun, educational, and well-organized outing. I‚Äôll definitely be returning soon!

name: Muebles Aurora
description: The worst customer service. I wanted to buy a piece of display furniture (the last one) that was old and badly damaged, and they wouldn't charge me a single cent. They only accept cash and it takes forever to process a simple purchase. It seems like you're going back in time in this business. The worst, the worst.

name: L¬¥Aurora Inn Hostal
description: Excellent! Comfortable, clean, and close to the airport. They offer free breakfast and transportation to the airport at any time.

name: Hotel Aurora
description: We enjoyed our stay in Antigua and this hotel was a great choice. The staff was very friendly and helpful and it was easy walking distance to everything. The included continental breakfast provides the basics but you can purchase other options (eggs, french toast, etc) at very reasonable prices. Clean, comfortable, and AC if you need it.

name: Budget Car Rental Aeropuerto Internacional La Aurora
description: We initially rented a full size SUV but had to switch to a larger van because the ‚Äúfull size‚Äù was a small SUV. It also had bald tires, so I didn‚Äôt feel safe driving that around. The van we rented was okay and I don‚Äôt have any complaints about that. After leaving the airport, we were stopped in traffic and a guy sideswiped us. Again, not a huge deal. We were required to carry FULL coverage. We called Budget and sent them photos and they cleared us to continue with our journey because it was only cosmetic damage. When we returned, they went over every inch of the car looking for additional scratches. There was none. Then he pulls out paperwork to file the claim with the insurance. I explained that we already reported to the insurance. I had to catch my flight, so he offered to have me sign the paperwork and he would fill out the information. I declined because I didn‚Äôt know what he would be writing in there after I signed the paperwork. If you have full coverage, then it should cover everything (even the scratches) without all the extra time spent. My friends rented through a different agency and they also got the full coverage. No 20 minute inspection before renting their car and no 30 minute inspection afterward. Go with a different company.

name: Hertz Guatemala ‚Ä¢ Aeropuerto Internacional La Aurora
description: Andy is such an amazing asset to the Hertz team. My family and I were on a Mountain - Volvano - Lake adventure in Guatemala and he really took his time to customize our rental needs!!!  Thank you!!!

name: Universal Renta Autos Aeropuerto, S.A.
description: Worst experience ever with a car rental company. The car we booked in for was not available at the pick-up location. They offered to upgrade it for a bigger and Pricer car that according to them was available at that time which we were okay with, but their system was not working and couldn't process the payment. We offer to pay cash for the deposit and leave our card information to be added into their system as soon as their system was restored but they said no. Had us there for over 2 hours waiting and left past midnight in a taxi with our children because there was nothing else they could do for us then. I honestly believe they did not have any of the cars they were promising us available. I do not recommend this business at all, and I will not be doing any business with them in the future. DO NOT waste your time. Go with Alamo or Enterprise. They're better and more reliable!

name: Hostal Aurora
description:
9/10 Excellent service, had 3 beds, fairly clean room, included breakfast.
Very friendly staff, we arrived without a reservation and the doors were very kindly opened to us. I recommend it and it has adequate parking

name: By Aura Hernandez

name: Sakala
description: SAKALA is doing a great job in Haiti, helping a lot of kids through Education, Agriculture and Sport. There is a very good learning environment at SAKALA for the kids every day. Thanks to Daniel Tillias who is the founder of Sakala and two other colleagues. I highly recommend people to come visit especially if you want to invest in education, sport and agriculture. Every body   is welcome at SAKALA, we need you, let's make a change together!

I haven‚Äôt been there ! But I appreciate the initiative to be selfless and help the country to go forward! The country needs more people like you guys ! Providing solutions and communities for the youth!
Well done !

name: Maison Acra

I got a great deal on two cuts of 4 way stretch knit fabric, as well as a gorgeous viscose print fabric. If you're ever in Petionville and are in need of fabric, school supplies, or other random household items, and speak Kreyol or French, I highly recommend dropping by.

name: AURA BEAUTY STUDIO
description: We went together to my daughter's for a blow-dry and manicure. The drying was more or less, the girl pulled me several times and when I asked her to detangle my hair she did it with the same brush that was drying my hair and not from tip to root, mistreating my hair. My daughter's experience with her manicure was bad, she wore a wine-colored gel which I did not remove completely, leaving traces. When painting again, the finish left a lot to be desired, the enamel contained quite a few bubbles and irregularities. Likewise, it lacked uniform coverage. The enamel was so thick that when I got home it started to fall off in places.  I attach photos

name: Aurora Park
description: So much potential here to develop something nice. Appears to be struggling. Decay is noticed on many areas. Still, nice place to meet with family and have a BBQ. Several canals of the lake have fallen trees over them and are blocking path for the people on canoes. Pools in good shape though. Oars for canoes all are busted. Kids enjoyed riding the horses.

name: apartamento aurora
description: Apartments with excellent size, contemporary finishes, security and privacy

name: Aura
description: Aura was an unexpected and incredible experience. They did not miss a beat. Almost feels like a VIP experience with how attentive the staff is and the club music. My compliments to the chef on making unique and large sushi rolls. Tasty appetizers. The drinks are crazy good. Excellent job and fun times in Honduras!

name: Blue Power Group Limited
description: Good customer service, try the Blue Power Super whites they're the best...üòäüëç

name: ROK Hotel Kingston, Tapestry Collection by Hilton
description: This was an amazing experience. The people at the hotel were second to none. I felt very secure there being a woman by myself. The pool was refreshing. The food was good but their dining room was quite expensive if you didn't want to leave there were not too many alternatives. It's probably why the dining room was all but empty, and many people went across the street to eat. The drinks were good, and I really enjoyed my view from the balcony in my room, and from the pool, and from the dining room. If you are staying in the area I would recommend them highly.

name: TRIO
description:
An Unforgettable Birthday Dinner at Trio!

I recently celebrated my birthday at Trio, and I have to say‚Äîit was nothing short of amazing. From the moment I walked in, the staff made me feel like royalty. Their attentiveness, professionalism, and warm energy truly elevated the entire experience.

We had a private room for the celebration, and the decoration was absolutely stunning. Every detail was thoughtfully arranged, creating an elegant and festive atmosphere that made the evening feel extra special.

The food? Absolutely delicious. Every dish was beautifully presented and bursting with flavor. It‚Äôs clear that Trio takes pride in both their cuisine and customer care.

If you‚Äôre looking for a place to celebrate a special occasion‚Äîor simply want a top-tier dining experience‚ÄîTrio is the place to be. I‚Äôm so grateful for the unforgettable memories, and I can‚Äôt wait to go back!

name: Alhambra Inn
description:
A stone's throw from the commercial district, Alhambra In is close enough for the convenience of being close enough for that lunch meeting but tucked away from the noise, hustle & bustle of the city.
The airy atmosphere of the restaurant also makes you forget how close you are to the stifling city. The friendly, courteous staff and the historic decor will make you feel right at home.
Facilities are clean and well- maintained. The staff is professional and friendly.

name: Reggae Mill Restaurant & Bar - OPA Greek Restaurant
description:
Went there on Sunday for a friend's birthday and it was a FANTASTIC experience. The owner Alexx possesses a charm and wit that makes it impossible not to laugh when he's around, and his excellent customer service makes you feel right at home.

Our waitress also did a spectacular job with delivering service with a smile and a playful energy.

The food was also simply top notch: the appetizers were superb and and the Lamb Burger is worth the slaughter of baby sheep üòÇ. Delicious

Overall, it's a restaurant with a great aesthetic, A-one customer service, and delectable foods. 12/10 would recommend for anyone who wants to enjoy not just great food, but an AWESOME experience.

name: Uncorked!
description:
My sorority sisters and I visited this restaurant for lunch while staying in Mo Bay a few weeks ago as we visited from the US to celebrate our 30th anniversary. Our food was ok. Some enjoyed more than others. I ordered the salmon balls (not pictured), they were bland. I also ordered the Oxtail Gnocchi which was much better. The pasta was a little mushy but I was able to push through as the overall dish had a good taste and the oxtail was cooked to my liking. My drink was pretty good.

I do however feel I would‚Äôve enjoined my meal more if I wasn‚Äôt nursing a sore wrist and knee while eating after toppling down two steps because of negligence of this establishment. We were a semi large group of 9 that was seated on an upper level. Unfortunately, I didn‚Äôt notice how close I was placed to the edge of the landing as I sat in the end seat as a trusting patron that never questioned the seating arrangement. It wasn‚Äôt until I attempted to get up to use the restroom by pushing my chair back did I meet my fate of toppling down two steps. I knocked over my glass of water on the way down, shattering it while my friends held the table to prevent it from falling on me. I left with a complimentary bag of ice for my sore wrist and a $78 (USD) bill as the manager, Chevel with no sign of remorse refused to comp my bill. The customer service leaves a lot to be desired, to say the least!

name: Aurora Ministries
description: Great worship experience üôå , friendly congregation and great teaching of the word of God

name: Shabria entertainment record label & Recording studio LLC
description: this studio is great  followed my friend there ,they are so professional

name: AURA VIIBE LIMITED
description: The experience at aura vibe is top tier, I went there and honestly I was a bit nervous but after talking to their rep I felt comfortable. based on the customer service experience it was very helpful and informative I can tell that they knew their stuff. They‚Äôre products were top tier and the prices were reasonable.

name: Chukka Lethe Village
description: Really beautiful raft ride. Paid $50 each for 4 adults and a kid (2 rafts) wonderfully friendly young men who work hard. Ride midpoint is a area they stop and do limestone massages. Quote $20 usd for feet and legs to the knee. Seems extremely popular with many local women getting full body limestone massages.

name: Chukka Caribbean Adventures
description:
I loved the experiences. I did the ATV/Dune Buggy, Zip Line and catamaran boat.

My ONLY major complaint is you spend a lot of time waiting around and I feel that could be resolved with assigned/reserved time slots.

The staff is fun, yet professional. I felt safe during each activity. I def will be returning my next Jamaica Trip!

name: Chukka Eco-Adventure Outpost at Good Hope
description:
This tour company round trip pick up from your hotel which is needed but I guess it is also a tour group stop so you will see groups of people coming off the boats.

The excursions were a lot of fun. The hive you a safety brief before getting started.
The scenery is really beautiful like being on a safari.
There are lockers available for $10.
There is a rum tasting every few hours and lots of history around the former sugar plantation.
There isn‚Äôt many options for food.
The bar is nice with a few friendly stray kittens walking around.
Bring cash to tip your driver and tour guides. Bring sun block and bug spray.

Really great experience overall.

name: Chukka Cove & Cliffs at Llandovery
description: What a beautiful place. The views alone are worth the visit. I enjoyed being blessed enough to spend time with family to build more forever memories ‚ù§Ô∏è

name: CHUKKA Adrenaline Outpost at White River Valley
description:
The waterfall portion of the tour was cool! It was fun to jump in the different pools, and it was beautiful. Our guides on the hike itself were helpful, but our guide on the bus and the driver were not very professional or kind. The woman on the bus told us we couldn‚Äôt go to the bathroom at the start of the hike but had to wait till the bottom because she wanted our group to leave fast. When we made it to the bottom they rushed us onto the hike and many people on the bus ended up holding it and waiting till much later to go to the bathroom.

On the ride back our bus driver was driving very crazily and actually rear ended a car! He smashed up the other persons car pretty good! He was driving very crazy the entire day and had some road rage that made us feel unsafe. The crash whipped our heads forward pretty good. Then when we got off the bus we tipped the tour lady what we had with the intent to get cash to tip her after going to the shops. She waved my wife and I  back over and said ‚Äúa tip this small is an insult in Jamaica‚Äù and glared at us. After getting in an accident and the lady being very unprofessional about the tip, we did not go find cash to tip her the way we would have liked to. It was a rather scary experience, hopefully she will be more patient and kind with paying customers in the future and the driver will drive safer.

The class ran from 9:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m., and we ended by sitting down for a delicious lunch with the whole group. It was such a wonderful, immersive day. I highly recommend this cooking class to anyone visiting Mexico City. It was truly one of the highlights of our trip!

name: The Westin Resort & Spa, Cancun
description:
Mixed Experience at a Beautifully Located Resort

The hotel boasts a prime beachfront location, but direct beach access is limited due to a cement wall, which takes away from the oceanfront experience. During our stay, the beach was covered in seaweed, which made it difficult to enjoy the shoreline.

On the positive side, the resort features stunning pools, including a fun wave pool that‚Äôs perfect for young children. The in-room amenities, like the refrigerator, worked well. However, I felt the overall service could have been more reflective of the local culture. The restaurant options leaned heavily toward Italian and pizza‚Äîperhaps appealing to some, but it left me wondering: who comes to Cancun for Italian food?

As longtime members of the hotel, our experience was especially bittersweet. A close family member dedicated over 30 years of service to this hotel, and yet, we felt the hospitality extended to us was less than what regular guests receive. It‚Äôs not a popular opinion, but I firmly believe employees and their families‚Äîwho have shown deep loyalty‚Äîshould be treated with exceptional appreciation and care.

The hotel‚Äôs location in the hotel zone is convenient, but traffic in the area can be heavy, making it difficult to explore. If you plan to stay on the property and enjoy familiar, American-style comforts, it‚Äôs a solid option. However, for those wanting a rich cultural experience, you‚Äôll need to venture into the city

name: Wyndham Grand Cancun All Inclusive Resort & Villas
description: From the moment we arrived, we were treated like royalty. The staff‚Äôs warmth, attention to detail, and genuine hospitality made us feel right at home. Our room was spotless, spacious, and offered breathtaking views that looked like something out of a travel magazine. The amenities were top-notch from the sparkling pools and pristine beach to the world-class spa and delicious dining options, every moment felt luxurious. The food was fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented, and the variety meant there was always something new to try. What truly stood out was the atmosphere: peaceful, relaxing, and absolutely stunning. Every corner of the resort felt like it was designed for pure enjoyment. I can‚Äôt recommend this resort enough  it‚Äôs the perfect blend of comfort, beauty, and exceptional service. I‚Äôll definitely be coming back!

description:
Very nice quiet family hotel. Pool area was great for my 2 year old - he loved the slide. Beach was amazing and there were always beach chairs available. They have two parrots that talk to you and my son also loved them. They also had a real crib that they provided to our room that was very comfy for my son and he slept well.

The hotel is close to many restaurants- some touristy ones and some authentic Mexican places that are much cheaper down the road. There is also a nice coffee shop and grocery store right by the hotel.

name: Casa Chakras
description:
My time at Casa Chakras was life-changing, to say the least. We were blessed that there were only two (full-time) students on our teacher training course, meaning we got the full care and attention of Miel and Alex. Casa Chakras is located around 20 minutes from the centre and is quite rural (in comparison to the busy town centre, which I would also recommend visiting).
The quiet tranquillity we found at Casa Chakras was the perfect partner to aid our learning experience, allowing us to fully immerse ourselves in the rich culture presented. We took a few trips to the beach, participated in a wonderful Mayan canoe tour, and swam in the local cenote (quite scary as I'd never swam in a place like it before, but very culturally significant so a must in my opinion); however, nothing topped the morning yoga classes or evening somatic practices we had each day.
I must also thank Ambar, who was one of the highlights of our trip! Her light and eagerness to be involved brought us right back to being girls, encouraging us to let loose and simply have fun, integrating the deep knowledge we gained through laughter, playing mermaids in the pool and dance parties.
Miel created such a safe place to deepen our yoga practice, connect to the spirit within us and acted as a wonderful role model on how we would like to live our lives. I am forever grateful to be welcomed into the Casa Chakra Ashram!
If you have any doubts about selecting Casa Chakra, just do it. The journey is tough as you are taught a lot of information in a short amount of time, and have your own memories and experiences come up, but it was one of the best decisions I have ever made.
Casa Chakra is a place to immerse yourself in the yogic life, to find peace coming out of your comfort zone and connect with yourself, it's, a safe haven.

name: Karrara Stone, SA
description:
Review for Karrara: Worst customer experience

I want to begin this review with a feeling of deep frustration and anguish. As a customer, I have had the misfortune of working with Karrara, and I can say without a doubt that it has been the worst experience I have had with any supplier in my entire life.

From the beginning, the company has demonstrated a complete lack of professionalism and commitment to established deadlines. The lies regarding delivery times and the arrival of materials were constant, which generated anxiety and confusion that I cannot describe in words. Every time I tried to get clear information, I found answers that were vague, evasive and completely far from reality. It's as if they don't care one bit about the well-being or peace of mind of their clients.

What finally broke my patience, however, was the negligent treatment I received in my own home, and the rude treatment I received from the team, and from Freddy (who says he is the owner of the company).

Not only did they fail to meet the quality standards I expected from a company that is supposed to be professional, but they also damaged my walls, floors, baseboards during the process.

Despite being informed of these damages, (by all means of WhatsApp, calls, etc.. where they do not answer for long periods of time... responding only with a "thank you for your patience", but even so they continue to leave me in the air) they did not take responsibility or show any willingness to repair the damage caused, leaving an even deeper feeling of distrust.

As a customer, I experienced constant anguish as my service expectations were increasingly overwhelmed by a totally different reality. Not only did they fail fundamentally, but they did so in such a contemptuous manner that it is difficult for me to understand how they continue to operate.

For all the above, my most sincere recommendation is that you avoid working with Karrara at all costs. Not only are they incompetent, but they lack any type of responsibility in their service. My intention with this review is not only to share my experience, but also to help other people not have to go through the same suffering and frustration that I experienced when trusting them. I don't want anyone else to be in the same distressing situation that I experienced.

We had an island tour later in the week, again in a beautiful smelling, clean and cool vehicle. We had a sudden downpour whilst out and all of us were soaking. Not a problem, there were plenty of clean towels for us to use.

I rented a car July 31st to August 4th.  I had a small issue with the car and called them on Saturday. The lady who answered the phone was on vacation, but ensured someone got back to me right away. The gentleman came and drove behind me to the Avis location. The customer care was impeccable, soothing voices, calm and assuring -- I got a new car and they provided me with comfort to reach out again. Their service was amazing, professional, comforting, reliable and caring.  The cars were nicely cleaned, spotless. Glad I rented from this location, it truly a beautiful experience!

I had some packages delivered to their warehouse since August 2024 and I am only collecting my packages today, December 5, 2024. When asked why my packages had not arrived as yet, all I got was ridiculous excuses. I will be updating this review with screenshots of emails so persons can see the mediocrity they‚Äôll have to put up with if they choose to ship with Hobson Enterprises. Up to this day, I have not been issued an apology for this extremely long delay in receiving my packages or a valid reason for the delay. And!!! These people were brave enough to attempt to charge me a storage fee of US$30 for having my packages in their warehouse for over a month even after I gave clear instructions to ship! The service at Hobson Enterprises is grossly distasteful! From the customer service and support to the long wait times to the ridiculous charges.

name: Park Hyatt St. Kitts Christophe Harbour
description: We stayed at Park Hyatt St Kitts as a family of 4 in early June. This resort is lovely. Beautiful grounds, spacious pools, small but nice beach. It was low season, so the resort was not crowded at all. Staff was attentive and responsive. Food, while pricey (remember, it's an island), was delicious. There was not a single meal we didn't rave about. There are a few beach restaurants that are easily walkable from the resort to offer other options and slightly lower price points. Our two kids, age 13 and 15, enjoyed the laid back atmosphere. They also enjoyed basketball in the pool, the trampoline in the ocean, and shuffleboard by the pool. A day trip around the island was easily organized with the concierge. The concierge also arranged transportation for us to and fro Dolphin Discovery. Truly, this is a lovely, luxurious, but laid back destination!

name: Mr. X‚Äôs Shiggidy Shack
description: Fun place to go. Right on the beach with a great swimming area. Food was good, I had the grouper, it was very good, light, perfectly cooked, veggies were so-so.  They had trivia night while we were there it was a lot of fun. Service was a little slow but super friendly.

name: Sunset Reef St. Kitts
description: Sunset Reef was absolutely stunning. The views from each room and infinity pool were spectacular. The pathways around this spacious boutique hotel were clean and beautifully designed with flora and fauna (monkeys in the back mango tree). Their restaurant, Drop Anchor Grill was top notch. Everything was freshly handmade and tasty. The rooms were spacious and decorated perfectly and supplied with all that we needed. The managers and staff were so accommodating and personable. Sunset Reef is great for a couple, a family, or even sharing with a bunch of your best friends and family. This place does not disappoint.

name: Caribelle Batik at Romney Manor
description: On a cruise, we stopped by St Kitts and got a driver to take us around the island. This was one of his suggestions, so we drove up the small, rough rainforest road. As we drive up, we see the ~500 year old tree. It was $3/per person to walk the grounds and it is well worth it. There are some beautiful landscapes that have views of the ocean below. After spending time feeling crammed on a cruise boat, it was finally nice to sit on a bench under this huge tree and hear nothing but nature around. The tapestries they made were beautiful and impressive. They are building a new viewing deck a little higher, but the views over the sugar mill were a different view than you get down by the beach to see the rainforest hills. Carib beers and rum punch are a little more expensive, but were refreshing on a warm summer day. I highly suggest stopping here if you are on the island for some peace and quiet time.

The spa itself is in a super convenient location (though parking can be tricky), and tucked into the back corner of the Vida Gym on U Street. As a member at the Vida, I was able to use my initiation fee credit towards a 60 minute massage ($130). Peter was my masseuse, and made my experience incredible. He was kind, communicative, and was able to give me an amazing very deep tissue massage, which I've had trouble finding therapists who are able to do so in the past. Would 100% come back to Peter at this location and would recommend others to do the same!

description:
I got my hair done here about 2-3 weeks ago (fresh & current below). I asked Lily for a lived in, old money brown, but as soon as she finished I just KNEW it would wash out to be this weird/gross reddy-orange. I literally told her that I was cool toned and it wouldn‚Äôt look good on me, but she just dismissed me and said I wear gold jewelry? Like I don‚Äôt know my own skin tone?
It was such an impersonal experience. When I first sat down, she IMMEDIATELY tried to sell me an $90 conditioner. She had 3-4 clients while I was there. Here‚Äôs the real kicker, she originally glazed my hair wrong, so she had to reglaze it (which is okay whatever I‚Äôm glad you‚Äôre fixing it) but after the reglaze they said I could either wait 30 minutes for someone to blow dry my hair or I could do it myself. I literally almost started sobbing in the salon, I felt so humiliated and embarrassed. After like 10 minutes, my (so so lovely and kind) hair washer came over to help me, I think because my eyes were watering.
The worst of all? I paid $350 AND THEY DIDNT EVEN CUT MY HAIR!!! Who does that?! I go to a lot of bougie salons because I love my hair and it‚Äôs like my self care, I have never been to one that doesn‚Äôt even include a trim? I‚Äôm for sure not going back, and I would encourage you to look else where as well. I wouldn‚Äôt wish this experience on my worst enemy.

description: I would love to stay at this hotel again whenever I visit NY and I highly recommend to others if you are on the fence! This hotel is in a nice central location to almost everything- Bryant Park, the NY library, Times Square, Central Park, and more! The food wasn‚Äôt good for the price. The staff seemed untrained ‚Äî not because they didn‚Äôt want to offer good service, but because they clearly lacked basic knowledge of proper restaurant service and the correct order of serving items.

name: Aurora
description:
Prominently located in Docklands, directly opposite the colourful National Australia Bank building, on the corner of Harbour Esplanade and Bourke Street, Aurora is an impressive highly reflective stainless steel sculpture by Melbourne Artist/Sculptor Geoffrey Barlett.  It's named after the Roman goddess of the dawn and its inverted cargo net makes a symbolic connection to Docklands‚Äô history as Victoria‚Äôs most important port. At night it's lit from within, creating an impression of a glowing orb floating above the pavement.

Docklands includes more than 45 pieces of public art and you can download Development Victoria's Harbourside Docklands Art Trail app to locate most of these.

I am really fuzzy with my hair and she got it perfectly! I highly recommend her and I couldn‚Äôt be happier with her work! Absolutely amazing! Thanks Emmaüòä

name: Chameleon New Age Salon
description:
This is the first time I'm leaving a negative review online, which is not easy for me because I really don‚Äôt want to discourage anyone from visiting this salon ‚Äì I think it‚Äôs a good one! I just want to share my experience because I would have appreciated seeing such a review before deciding to get my hair layered.üôÇ

The salon has a really friendly atmosphere, and Charlotte is certainly a skilled specialist in many treatments and haircuts. Unfortunately, my experience with layering didn‚Äôt go well.

I have thick, frizzy, and slightly curly hair, so I asked for volume reduction and layering. I also showed a photo as inspiration (it's included in the attached photos). Charlotte assured me she could do it.

During the haircut, I noticed that the hair was being cut too high, so I expressed my concerns. Charlotte suggested that I "trust the process," which I did. In the end, I asked for a bit of adjustment to the front, based on what I could see.

I waited two weeks before writing this review, trying to get used to the hairstyle, but my hair just looks odd ‚Äì it‚Äôs cut at different lengths and doesn't resemble the photo I showed at all. On the bright side, my head does feel lighter now, but that‚Äôs the only positive thing about my new haircut. The only thing I can do now is wait for it to grow out so I can fix it.

Charlotte, you're truly great‚ò∫Ô∏è ‚Äì just not at layering hair.

the room is clean and neat, it‚Äôs pretty decent. The service is great. The resort opens on Sundays which is great since only a few place is opened and we can just chill around the pool and dine in in the resort restaurant (I had fish and chips for a dinner and it was okay).

The only issue was the hotel has very very thin walls so you can kinda hear people walking and passing by your room. There were parties and people laughing / talking pretty loudly until midnight (by the pool or next door) - which happened every day of the week I was there. They also blasted some music early in the morning (sometimes).

That‚Äôs the downside but everything else is great. Especially the location - it‚Äôs close to the main street and all the restaurants.

name: Leiola
description: If you are looking for a good selection of wine in Tongatapu, then this is the place to go! There was a great selection of wine, beer, and spirits at reasonable prices. The shop also sells upmarket items like perfume and makeup. The shop was very well-presented, clean and tidy. The staff wore uniforms and were very attentive. Card is accepted here.

name: Ma'ufanga
description: Nice atmosphere, background n scenery

name: Lulutai Airlines Ltd.
description:
Avoid This Airline ‚Äì Worst Travel Experience Ever

I strongly advise against flying this airline. My 30-hour journey from Tampa to Tonga ended in complete frustration due to their unprofessionalism and lack of customer care.

After finally arriving in Tongatapu, I had one short flight left to reach my destination for a once-in-a-lifetime swimming-with-whales experience. This final flight was critical‚Äîbut the airline caused me to miss the first day of my trip.

Before traveling, I contacted the airline to confirm my connection time was sufficient. I received no reply until after the incident, when a supervisor casually emailed saying I ‚Äúshould have plenty of time.‚Äù

I reached the domestic terminal with 20 minutes to spare‚Äîtight, but the plane was still on the runway. Staff refused to let me board, claiming it would create 30 minutes of extra paperwork. When I asked to take the 4:00 PM flight, I was told it had been canceled three days earlier.

They offered me a flight the next morning instead, making me miss the first day of my whale experience. When I asked for a hotel voucher, they refused, and the airport closed for the night‚Äîleaving me stranded in the rain. I had to rely on the kindness of a stranger to find a hotel, which was unsafe and unpleasant.

Despite multiple calls and emails, no one has responded to confirm whether I will be refunded for my unused return flight. I am still paying for it, and the airline refuses to communicate. I ultimately paid $500 to rebook my return through Fiji at my own expense.

This airline has been in the media repeatedly for aviation, compliance, and safety issues since it began operations in 2020. Tonga‚Äôs civil aviation authority even suspended their maintenance certificate due to a lack of qualified engineers. Their service is as alarming as their safety record.

I will never fly this airline again, and I sincerely hope it goes out of business soon.

name: Tungi Colonnade Hotel
description:
Despite all the negative reviews prior to booking our family of 4 with Tungi for 5 nights during heilala week to experience the atmosphere during the festival season and it was great.
We booked a double room for 2 kids and two adults for $200 pa‚Äôanga a night that‚Äôs $130 aus. The receptions accommodated us with a late check in when our flight landed at 12:30am. Made a deposit prior to arrival and for a family member to pick up our keys.
The rooms was specious and eve though it wasn‚Äôt as clean compare to other hotels it‚Äôs a budget room and understandable it‚Äôs Tonga. My husband and I just bought cleaning products from the shop the next day and spring cleaned and mopped the whole room and bathroom and disinfect everything and sprayed mortien all around before we settled.
Our kids loved the cold showers everyday, and the fact they could walk downstairs to buy the best  bbq on the street was an experience for them. Everything was a walking distance and convenient that we didn‚Äôt have to hire a care. We loved our stay especially the church bells on Sundays.

name: Ancient Tonga
description: Fascinating 2 hours session introducing Tonga culture and history, way of life, using plants as herbal cues, medicine and food, traditional weapons and utensils, and more. The session was conducted in a lively and interactive manner. The museum showcased intricate art, traditional costumes, and artifacts. Included a good lunch too

Love Tonga power and what they do!
In an emergency  or general power cut whether planed or not, no communication! Numbers provided are a shot in the dark. Don't waste your time calling as they just hang up on you! So very disappointed and left in the dark! Kinda expected for a developing country!.....

name: Cafe Escape
description: Food was good. Panini was big enough. Service is a bit slow, but that‚Äôs just something standard for most of the places.

name: Tonga Chamber of Commerce & Industry Inc
Mum's Cafe Nukualofa
description:
I ordered the Fisherman - which is Ita Oka, Fried Fish, green salad and a choice of sweet potato/rice.

Ita Oka is great, but could have more tomato or cucumber for more acidity. Portion is huge which is very filling!

My friend got seafood pasta and he liked it!

name: Lava Cafe & Takeaway
description:
One of my favorite places to eat on the island. Recommend fish and chips, fish is tuna caught off the island.

Staff super friendly. Great atmosphere and decor. They also sell savory and sweet items along with coffee.

Enjoyed so much became my go to place while in the Kingdom.

name: 21st Century Electronics
description: Very friendly and helpful. Electronics, phones and battery replacement services.

name: Highway Superrette & Bakery
description: Purchased 3 breads from here. The popular coconut bread which was my favourite, absolutely delicious. Ube bread which is a kumala/kumara/sweet potato bread which was also sweet and delicious. And lastly the cinnamon bread which was sticky, sweet and delicious. Came another time and got the famous ice cream in a half loaf of coconut bread and it was amazing.

name: South Seas Rum
description: Best Punch and Alchahol in Tonga

name: 'Oholei Beach Resort
description: Beautiful experience of Tongan traditions, music, stories and food. My 3 year old daughter loved her time and we were made to feel most welcome.

name: EZ TONGA ONLINE SHOPPING
description: I sent food for my inlaws & sisters through this website and they all received it with no problems. I highly recommend & will continue to use this service. Malo aupitoüôè

name: Si'i Kae Ola Supermarket
description: The display could be better however, you‚Äôll find some good quality products for a reasonable price here! A few items were already expiring but still with normal prices! So watch out!

name: AURORA KAVA BAR - NAMBURU
description: Came here to get kava to try. Were there around 4pm+ so not many people basically. Due to just finished lunch we bought small bottle of kava (300 vatu) home to try later. Not bad.

name: Volcanic Earth
description:
My wife and I were just married in Vanuatu and while we were over for our wedding as we always do in van we went to volcanic earth we had a couples massage and a couples hot stone massage a couple of days later. The massage was absolutely perfect. Pressure and motions were spot on. That alone would be enough, then add the products the scent and feel is out of this planet. Then add made in Vanuatu with natural products. What else do you need. The therapist are warm and caring. We had to organise for all our guest to have treatments also and Linda very approachable and responsive ensuring all our guests had the kind of treatments we have experienced there throughout our many trips over.
A little cheat code my wife used this trip was booking us for massage before our flight.

name: Volcanic Earth Day Spa
description: Staying in Port Vila for week and my friend and I had a wonderful afternoon at Volcanic Earth. We indulged with the Ash Me Tender package to try the volcanic wrap and hot stone massage and it didn‚Äôt disappoint. After soaking in a final bath of coconut oil my dry skin has never felt so good. Felia gave me a wonderful massage and facial. Staff were friendly and respectful. Would really recommend!

name: Vanuatu Craft Association
description: Great little shop. I didn't have the time to do a tour but the lady in the store was amazing and she let me try the drinks I was interested in buying. The coffee liquor is amazing, I have drank the Tanna coffee and now I have the liquor.  I am a very happy man. Recommend trying the local drops.

name: South Pacific Memories
description:
My partner and I had the most incredible stay here for 5 nights. The whole place is absolutely beautiful, the gardens, dining areas, pool and walkways are all so well looked after. We were actually surprised by how spacious it felt. With only four bungalows spread out across the property, each with its own lovely garden space, it never felt crowded. They easily could have fit more, but the choice to keep it small and peaceful really made a difference.

Anne and Petter were absolutely lovely, so welcoming and accommodating, and they really went out of their way to make sure we had everything we needed. Laura and Ed were also fantastic, full of great advice for things to do, and all the other staff were equally helpful and friendly.

The food was beautiful, with so much care put into using fresh local produce meaning every meal felt really special. And having the beach literally out the front was perfect. The reef starts just meters off the shore, and the amount of marine life right there was amazing with so many fish and corals, and all the snorkeling gear was provided (and really good quality too). As keen snorkelers, having such easy access to the reef was a huge highlight.

We also loved being just outside of town ‚Äî far enough to be peaceful and quiet, but still only a quick bike ride or bus trip into town when we wanted.

We honestly couldn‚Äôt recommend this place more, and would love to come back one day!

name: Breakas Beach Resort
description: The staff make this place special.  They remember your name and room number  are all very polite and helpful, I can't thank everyone enough for making our stay memorable. I had a massage, which was wonderful, and left feeling totally relaxed. The breakfast had a great selection of cereal,  bread, fresh fruit, and pancakes. The menus for lunch and dinner had a fantastic selection and something for everyone.  Pizzas were great, the beef burger was so tasty, and the pasta was amazing.  Had a desert a couple of nights, and it was delicious. The resort has no paved paths it is just sand everywhere, so it can make walking slightly difficult if you have any leg/feet issues. We stayed in a beachfront room and loved waking up to the sound of the waves but it can also be noisy in the evenings  if u are in close proximity to the restaurant/bar area as there is often music or entertainment happening. The room was cleaned every day, and housekeeping staff were accommodating with any specific requests we had. The bathroom was basic, but all you needed and loved the shower that was open air. The grounds are well maintained with raking every day.  Very much enjoyed the Wednesday night dinner and show and also Friday night fire  show.

name: The Havannah Vanuatu
description: Magical. If you‚Äôre looking for a total breakaway with your special someone, this is it. The staff genuinely care about your welfare and comfort. The food is amazing. The setting can‚Äôt be more idyllic. The peace was amazing. From maintenance, to housekeeping, to restaurant, and management, the whole team could not be more welcoming.

name: Rockwater Resort
description: Rockwater Resort is truly a slice of heaven.  The resort and grounds are stunning.  The staff are beautiful and the service exceptional.  Our suites were amazing!  Our meals were all delicious and our suites spotlessly clean.  Be sure to explore!  There‚Äôs a walk down to the water, where you swim through a cute little cave and out into the sea.  We saw incredible coral, fish, and a spotted ray swam right past us!  Just breathtaking.  Rockwater is the perfect place to stay and explore the incredible island of Tanna.

name: Le Life Resort, Vanuatu
description:
We had a great stay at Le Life, everyone was very welcoming and friendly, and they serve excellent food at good prices, especially recommend the ceviche!
The little beaches are beautiful and quiet and the snorkelling is good. We stayed in one of the 4 bed fares and it was lovely and cool, and beautifully presented.
We didn‚Äôt do any of the tours as we only stayed two nights but heard from others that they were fantastic!

name: Kia Orana Villas and Spa
description: We had the most wonderful stay at Kia Orana Villas.  Our Villa was clean, comfortable and had everything we needed.  It was such a a pleasure to meet our kind hosts, Sane and Joseph, thank you for your hospitality.  We will definitely be back!   ü•∞

name: CITC Duty Free
description:
If you want to pay over the top for your alcohol, shop at the CITC duty free shop at the airport.

However before you do, it would certainly pay to check the prices at the little outlet next door. SAVA Duty Free are by far cheaper for the same products .

Example:-

Coruba was $45.00 at CITC, at SAVA it was $29.00

Famous Groose was $34.00 and SAVA $23.00

Absolute vodka CITC 2 for $69.00 vs SAVA 2 for $50.00.

Check it out.

name: Pizzeria Italiana
description: Found this little gem on my 9 day holiday to the Cooks. I‚Äôve returned no less than 3 times during my stay on the Island. Really authentic traditional pizza made with high quality ingredients and care. Always greeted with a smile, couldn‚Äôt recommend this place enough if you fancy a taste of Italy on your journey.

name: Crown Beach & Spa Resort Rarotonga
description: I have recently returned from the Cook Islands where I spent a most memorable 9 day stay at the Crown Beach Resort.  All the staff at the resort were amazing, nothing was too much trouble for them to assist with any requests.  The dining area including the bar was fantastic.  Try the "Island Sunrise", you will fall in love!  The Villa's are comfortable, clean and provide everything you need.  I highly recommend you jump on a plane and go to experience paradise, one of God's miracles.  The people who live on the island are happy, welcoming and always smiling.  I intend to return next year.  I fell in love, and you will too!

name: SACHARUNA Shamanic Healing Retreats
description:
We spent three days at the Wizard Mountain Healing Center near La Paz - an incredibly beautiful, peaceful experience. We were warmly welcomed by Miguel and his family and immediately felt at home. Our accommodation was a cozy cabin in the middle of nature, surrounded by mountains, peace and a very special energy.

We ate together with the family every day, which created a warm, familiar atmosphere. The mood at the retreat was consistently relaxed, mindful and supportive. The daily meditations and preparatory exercises for the ceremony really helped me to find inner peace. Although I had hardly any previous experience with meditation, I felt well guided and safe.

The ayahuasca ceremony itself took place in Miguel's house - at first I was surprised, but it quickly became clear that this protected, intimate space was exactly the right place for such a profound experience. Miguel is a very sensitive, experienced shaman. He manages to hold the necessary space with great calm and at the same time be present when support is needed.

During the ceremony, I was able to experience unexpected insights - including memories from my childhood that I had long forgotten. It was healing, deeply moving and I felt safe and in good hands at all times. Even the day after, although our stay was officially over, Miguel warmly invited us to lunch together.

Whether you are experiencing an ayahuasca ceremony for the first time or already have experience, I can wholeheartedly recommend the Wizard Mountain Healing Center and Miguel's work. I am very much looking forward to my next visit.

-Max

name: Pegasus Suites & Corporate Center (New Wing)
description:
Most hotels were booked due the cricket finals in Guyana.
We booked at the Pegasus which didn‚Äôt have the best reviews.

Pleasant surprise when we got there - A ROOM WITH A VIEW! Our room was an executive suite with grand bathroom. An extra toilet for visiting guests.
Kitchen and upgraded lights and smart TVs.
Free breakfast at the original Pegasus, which was authentic Guyanese cuisine.

name: Pegasus Hotel - Old Wing
description:
Pegasus has two buildings, one is brand new and the other is ancient.
I went last year, since I have to travel to Guyana often for work, and I mentioned it was my 1st. Time staying there (I usually stay with their competition).
They told me I was getting a nice room in the new building in order to make me come back, and it was a great room indeed.
I enjoyed it so much that I booked there again, but this time they gave me a room at the ancient building.

And what a terrible experience!!!

All furniture looks from the 70's, sheets are almost transparent, and even the smell was so bad that they had to put little scent trees hanging all over the room and bathroom.
I complained with management, but they didn't show any interest in putting some effort into helping me.
And this is exactly how you lose a customer.
I'm never coming back to this hotel, and unless you make sure that your reservation is made at the new building, DO NOT GO THERE!!!...

JP

description: Our party of seven made a same-day reservation and were accepted. We arrived an hour late with an extra guest, and the staff were incredibly kind and still accommodated us. The food was delivered quickly, and everyone enjoyed their meal. Our drinks also arrived promptly and were very enjoyable. The restaurant was beautiful and had a great atmosphere. There was no music playing, and we saw a very large group (more than 15 people) being accommodated.

name: Java Coffee Bar & Bistro
description:
Don‚Äôt waste your money.

I don‚Äôt usually go to Java but this day I went out of pure desperation (it was raining, I was staying nearby and I wanted food for my baby).

There were two customers ahead of me (one having just pastries, the other a small pick up order) and it took over 20 minutes to get two slices of soggy toast and extremely dry eggs costing $2000 (this price does not include the coffee). The price wouldn‚Äôt have offended me if the food had any quality.  Unfortunately, Java does not offer quality. My 1 year old, who loves eggs and toast, did not eat this food. I did not either.

The barista was pleasant and made a decent latte. It was lukewarm but I could tell she was scared to burn the milk so I just let that slide. It was good foam. I don‚Äôt like their coffee bean (personal preference). It‚Äôs the sour+bitter aftertaste of green coffee beans.

Also, please tell me you see the hair/eyelash on the cucumber for extra flavor!

Just go to Oasis cafe, they‚Äôre not as money-hungry as Java seems to be.

name: Chacras Travel Peru
description: Had an absolutely wonderful trip to Palcoyo Rainbow Mountain at the end of March. Isaac was such a great driver and tour guide for our day long trip out there. He drove us through some beautiful countryside and let us take all the pictures we wanted and told us a ton of information. The whole day was filled with fantastic sights and the rainbow mountain was so cool. Because we left a little later in the morning than others, we ended up being alone at the top of mountains. Isaac took great care of us and let us take our time with everything. Highly recommend this tour company and Isaac!

name: Willka T'ika Essential Wellness
description:
This retreat is absolutely magical. The hospitality, food, rooms, gardens, and overall ambience made our visit tremendously unforgettable.

Delicious vegetarian breakfast and dinner are included and allowed us to taste fresh offerings from the on-site gardens - which are some of the most beautiful I've ever seen. In the dining room, we ate with other travelers, which was an absolute treat. We met lovely people. Also in the dining area, there was always hot water and herbs from the garden available for authentic tea.

The rooms are fantastic, including wonderful showers. The rooms are clean and roomy. We stayed during the South American winter, and every night the staff placed two hot water bottles in our sheets. What a treat!

Speaking of the staff, they were professional, polite, and effective.

We were fortunate enough to experience the outdoor hot water baths with Jasmine and eucalyptus leaves. They were unforgettable.

I really can't say enough about what a wonderful place Willka T'ika is.
